title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Mix soup with 2 cans of water measured in soup cans.
Pour over chicken and bake for about thirty minutes at 325°.
Turn over and cook about 25 to 30 minutes, depending on size of fryer.
This also does good in microwave.

title: norma jean's "play" dough(biscuit dough)
directions: Cut 1/2 cup either canola or olive oil into flour mixture. (Olive oil is recommended for heart patients.)
When cut in sufficiently, yeast should be ready to add to flour mixture, also adding buttermilk.

title: chicken mushroom stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes; brown in 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet. Transfer to a slow cooker. In the same skillet, saute the mushrooms, onion, zucchini, green pepper and garlic in remaining oil until crisp-tender. Place in slow cooker. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings. Cover and cook on low for 4 hours or until the vegetables are tender. Yield: 6 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat 1 minute.
Pour into loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Preheat oven at 325° to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: african violet formula
directions: One lemon a day baked whole in the oven in a dish with a little water.
Pierce the lemon, run into a glass of water, sweeten.
Too strong for stomach until you have eaten a few mouthfuls; then take some.
Recipe from Favorite Recipes of Orleans County.

title: survival chili
directions: Brown meat in a large sauce pot.
Add all other ingredients; simmer for 4 hours.

title: clam fritters
directions: Mix all together and fry in hot grease.

title: western style pot roast
directions: In heavy pot, brown meat on all sides in oil.
Add onion and cook until golden.
Combine ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over meat.
Simmer, uncovered, until meat is tender, about 3 hours.
Serve sliced with sauce along with onions, carrots and potato chucks if desired.
Serves 8.

title: depression potato soup
directions: Cover with water and cook until potatoes are almost done and drizzle dumplings into potatoes.
Cook until dumplings are not doughy.

title: party cucumber spread
directions: Coarsely shred enough cucumber to make 1 cup.
Press shredded cucumber between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir prepared cucumber and remaining ingredients into cream cheese.
Serve spread on party rye bread.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with all ingredients in a blender. Chill several hours before serving.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook rice and combine with meat mixture.
Cut lid off green peppers; remove stems and seeds.
Wash and dry peppers well.
Stuff peppers with meat and rice mixture.
Press pepper lids in place and cover with spaghetti and tomato sauce.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Microwave on Medium-low 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add ingredients in layers in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini bake
directions: In bowl, combine cottage cheese, 1/2 cup

Cheddar, eggs, oregano, salt and pepper. Spoon into greased shallow baking dish. Arrange zucchini, squash and tomato in alternating, overlapping fashion to cover egg mixture. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Sprinkle remaining Cheddar and bread crumbs on top; dot with butter. Bake for 10 more minutes to brown. Cut into squares to serve.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Cream sugars with shortening until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add coconut.
Mix in flour, baking powder, soda, salt and vanilla. Fold in cereal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute butter, onion, celery and carrots.
Add broth, soup, cheese and parsley.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add sour cream. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add sherry and serve immediately.

title: individual cheesecakes(use miniature muffin pans.)
directions: Mix these ingredients in mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat egg whites and fold into cheese mixture.
Butter your pans generously.
Put 1 tablespoon of graham cracker crumbs in each muffin cup and shake until all sides are well coated.
Fill each one almost full of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out of muffin pans as they cool for indentation.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Combine ingredients until mushy.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pistachio-coconut surprise
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add coconut and pineapple with juice and stir until well blended.
Spoon into loaf pan and freeze until firm or refrigerate until good and cold.
Dip pan into warm water, unmold onto plate and slice if you freeze it.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir to mix well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: yon mazeniti
directions: Brown onions, meat, bell peppers, celery and garlic in small amount of olive oil. Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients in a large pan. Bake 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Serves 12 or more.

title: ginger cheese ball
directions: Mince ginger and work into the cheese. Roll the ball in the chopped parsley. Wrap the cheese ball tightly in plastic wrap, excluding all air.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles a coarse meal.
Remove 1 cup mixture and combine with cinnamon and nuts. Set aside.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak the beans in cold water (to cover) overnight.
Cook beans in ample water with the baking soda.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Place the onion in the bottom of a 3-quart casserole. Add half the bacon, the beans and remaining bacon.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over the beans.
Add enough water to barely cover.
Do not stir!!

title: mushroom and cream lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne and put aside.
In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add mushrooms (sliced), garlic and lemon juice. Saute until tender.
Stir in flour, cream, milk and salt.
Cook over medium heat.
Keep stirring while it slowly boils and sauce thickens.
Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex pan: sauce, lasagne, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple smokies
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour, mustard, pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add sausages.
Cook for 5 minutes or until heated through.

title: fettucine carbonara
directions: Prepare fettucine according to package.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook bacon about 5 minutes until crisp. With slotted spoon, remove bacon and drain on paper towels.
Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in bacon drippings, for about 5 minutes.
Stir in cream, reduce heat to low and cook 1 to 2 minutes.

title: spoon yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add a pinch of sugar to the yeast water; set aside.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Dissolve both jellos in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cold juice from fruit.
Mix fruit and add to hot liquid.
Pour in large oblong pan.
Cover completely with marshmallows.
Whip 1 pint cream and fold in 1 cup Miracle Whip.
Spread over the marshmallows.
Sprinkle grated cheese over this to look like coconut.
Make day ahead.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add milk and egg yolks.
Beat. Mix flour, graham crackers, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Creole Frosting or serve with whipped cream.

title: cole-ferrell salad
directions: Toss all ingredients gently in a bowl.
Chill and serve. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and stir all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Let set in refrigerator.
Makes 16 to 20.

title: turkey vegetable burgers(low-fat!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon water over medium-high heat for 3 to 5 minutes, until water evaporates.
Add celery and saute, stirring, for 3 minutes to soften.
If vegetables begin to stick, add additional water as needed.

title: no-chop potato salad
directions: In 3 or 4-quart saucepan, cook potatoes with onion and pepper in large amount of boiling water, covered, 6 to 8 minutes or until potatoes are tender; drain well.
In large bowl, combine cooked potatoes and celery; set aside.
In small bowl, combine dip, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Add mayonnaise mixture to potato mixture; toss lightly to coat.
Gently fold in eggs.
Turn into 2 or 2 1/2-quart moisture and vapor proof serving container (Tupperware).
Cover; chill several hours or overnight. Best served within 3 hours (keep chilled).
Makes 20 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Turn out onto damp dish towel and roll.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Remove seeds from pepper; stuff with cheese.
Roll sausage around peppers.
Place on broiler pan in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Roll biscuit dough around sausage. Place in oven until biscuits are done, about 20 minutes.

title: deviled pecans
directions: Melt margarine; add salt, onion salt and chili powder.
Stir in pecans, coating well.
Spread in single layer on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain and cool on paper towel. Store in airtight container.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, onions and garlic; cook until meat is brown. Drain fat.
Stir in flour.
Add soup, mushrooms (drained), salt and pepper to taste; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through. Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters and roll into balls.
Shake each piece into a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
When covered, place in a greased angel food cake pan.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Cook until it boils.
Pour this over the biscuits already in pan.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn out on plate.
Best served warm.

title: spasta supreme
directions: Cook and drain rotini.
Add remaining ingredients (chopped). Mix together.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into dry ingredients.
Add egg to vinegar and water; stir all together and divide into 4 portions individually and use as needed.

title: onion-mushroom rice
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
When onion is tender, add the uncooked rice.
Brown over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add skillet mixture to bouillon in baking dish.
Season to taste. Cook, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: crunchy cheeseroni
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add soups, green pepper, pimento and cooked macaroni.
Place half the mixture in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half the cheese and onions.
Top with remaining macaroni mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make a white sauce with butter, flour and gradually add chicken broth.
Stir constantly until thick. Add chili powder.
Dip tortillas in sauce to soften.
Place cheese, chicken and onion in center of tortilla and roll up. After all enchiladas are made, add sour cream to sauce and pour over top.
Top with paprika and grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: paprika chicken(serves 4)
directions: Combine salt, pepper, sage and paprika.
Rub over chicken. Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix milk, butter, cheese, flour, salt, pepper and soups over low heat.
Layer
potatoes,
ham
and onions, then repeat again. Then pour mixture over
the top.
Bake until heated through good, 1 hour at 350°. Serves 20 to 25.

title: fresh strawberry milk shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and keep in airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup of mix to 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows if desired.

title: jodi's apple turnovers
directions: Mix ingredients; let come to a boil.
Set off heat and allow to cool.
Take crescent dinner rolls, one section at a time, and spoon apple mixture in half center and fold top of roll over.
Use a fork to pinch around sides to seal in mixture.
Fry in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: favorite cheese pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread cookies
directions: Mix sugars and butter.
Add flour; mix until moist and crumbly.
Knead dough lightly until it holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten. Bake 45 minutes at 275° until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheets. Cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour with milk, eggs (one at a time) and vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: glazed salmon
directions: Combine oil, molasses, garlic and lemon rind. Mix well. Place salmon in shallow dish. Add marinade, turning to coat on all sides. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours, turning often. Broil or barbecue salmon, starting skin side down and turning once, 3 to 4 minutes per side or until fish flakes easily. Brush often with marinade.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: In casserole, mix all ingredients; add chicken breasts.
Cover loosely and microwave 25 minutes on High, or bake in conventional oven at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nat mix
directions: Mix together and store in container.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth and almost fluffy.
Pour into glasses and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: on stove peanut brittle
directions: Cook on medium temperature until peanuts pop, then turn off. Add heaping teaspoonful soda and one teaspoon salt.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Beat egg with sugar and cinnamon.
Add melted oleo; mix well and add grated apples.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve on toast or bread pieces.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix sweetened milk and Cool Whip.
Add lemonade.
Mix and pour into pie crusts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons butter; add flour and salt.
Add milk slowly; cook until sauce thickens.
Add sliced potatoes; bring to a boil.
Put into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and dot with remaining butter.
You can use a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in orange peel, orange juice and egg, just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove.
Cool completely before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf. One slice equals 85 calories and 2 grams of fat.
A great low calorie breakfast bread!

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and cook on low heat for 15 minutes until onions are soft.
Transfer to large saucepan. Add bouillon and 3 cans water, seasoning and parsley.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and cover.
Let simmer about 20 minutes.
Roughly grate hard cheese.
Serve soup in heated bowls or mugs and pass cheese and croutons.

title: sweet potato souffle crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into greased baking dish in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: margaret's zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion for 5 minutes.
Drain well. Mix in sour cream and soup.
Mix stuffing and butter.
Put most of crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save some for top.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: In skillet, heat oil and 4 tablespoons butter.
Add onion and parsley; mix well.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Remove cover.
Turn up heat to medium.
Add livers, garlic and wine.
Cook until livers are just done and wine has evaporated.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper (if desired).
Set aside to cool.
In food processor or blender, puree mixture to paste.
As you process, add 6 tablespoons melted butter.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon, shape into a ball and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 7 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans and ketchup together.
Combine onion, sugar, mustard and A.1. together.
Sprinkle over beans and top with bacon strips. Bake at 325° for 1
to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cream sugar and butter; mix in egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture. Stir in nuts, apples, water and vanilla.
Put in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Serve warm or cold with vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.

title: hobo salad
directions: Mix all together.
Do the night before.

title: banana split cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking pan with foil. Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar together.
Press into bottom of baking pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with an electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Stir in mashed banana.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with strawberries, banana and pineapple. Sprinkle with nuts.
Drizzle with semi-sweet baking chocolate. Cut into bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a large spoon.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back.
Makes 2 to 3 layer cakes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour containing all dry ingredients. beat water, egg and vinegar together.
Add to flour mixture and stir until moist.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Also, may be frozen for a later time.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Blend well.
Stir in buttermilk, add beaten eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until firm when tested in the center.

title: harvard beets
directions: Can substitute Sweet 'N Low for sugar.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: Brown roast on all sides; add sauerkraut with juice, brown sugar and bay leaf.
Cover tightly and simmer 4 to 6 hours.

title: jerky
directions: Marinate 6 to 12 hours in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Stir occasionally.
Dry in dehydrator or very low set oven (leave door open slightly).

title: honey-mustard pork roast
directions: In a bowl, combine the ginger ale, mustard, honey, oil, garlic and rosemary. Place the roast in a large resealable plastic bag; add marinade. Seal bag and turn to coat. Refrigerate for least 2 hours.

title: chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and chocolate in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until comes to a vigorous boil.
Let boil 1 minute. Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper until cool.

title: mrs. mcintyre's "dessert"
directions: Combine Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple and cut up peaches to milk-Cool Whip.
Fold in. Add lemon juice (to gel) and fold in. Refrigerate until jelled. Serve cold.
Just delicious.

title: artichoke nibblers
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil of 1 jar artichokes.
Cut up artichokes and saute with onion and garlic.
Beat eggs; add cheese and all other ingredients.
Mix.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.
(Can freeze.)

title: lena's greek-style squash
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until squash is tender; drain.
Set aside.
Combine ricotta cheese and next 4 ingredients.
Set aside.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Cook onion in oil a few minutes, add garlic and cook slightly (do not brown).
Add tomatoes, crushed to taste, and 2 cans water. Add seasonings, parsley, oregano and salt.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes, covered.
Add frozen spinach; cook just until done.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli (add no water) until all juice is gone. Slightly saute onion in butter and add this mixture to broccoli. Add garlic cheese, cut into chunks.
Add drained mushrooms and soup (undiluted).
Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: fresh peach rolls
directions: In baking dish, melt oleo.
Bring sugar and water to a boil in saucepan.
Prepare dough from flour, shortening, baking powder, salt and milk.
Roll thin and place peaches on dough.
Roll it up. Slice and place in baking dish.
Pour boiling mixture over roll dough and peaches.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saut onion and celery in margarine. Mix together olives, pimentos and cream. Cut chicken into bite size pieces and add other ingredients.
May add some broth from chicken to add moisture. Place into baking dish and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until cheese is melted and all ingredients are heated.
This dish freezes well!

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Boil your chicken. Take the chicken out and debone and cut up in little bits.
Take the remaining juice and add 2 cups of water, onion, Veg-All, chicken and bouillon and bring to a boil.
You may add more water if needed.
When it comes to a boil, take the biscuits and pinch off little pieces.
Add to the pot.
Cover and turn down to simmer.
Try not to stir too often because the dumplins won't rise if you open the lid a lot.
Add salt and pepper to the recipe as you desire.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and onion until creamy. Fold in crabmeat.
Put it on a dish covered with cocktail sauce. Surround with Wheat Thins and watch it disappear.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add margarine and milk; mix well. Cook on high until candy thermometer reaches 230°.
Turn off fire and add walnuts and vanilla. Beat for about 5 minutes or until mixture thickens!
Pour into well-greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch glass dish!
Pam works well!
Let cool and cut into squares! Store in tightly closed container!
Freezes well!

title: cheddar-vegetable chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute garlic, onion and mushrooms in butter over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes or until onion is softened.
Add flour and blend over low heat for 1 minute.
Slowly stir in half and half and chicken broth.
Cook, still stirring, until slightly thickened and smooth.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Gradually add grated Cheddar, blending until cheese is melted.
Add ham, Worcestershire sauce, broccoli, carrots, corn and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat chowder over moderately low heat until hot.
Do not let boil.
Serve immediately.

title: ham-in-a-can
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove key from the canned ham.
Punch holes around top edge of can with punch-type can opener, every inch or so all around the can.
Place
ham in oven and bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven and pour juice out of can through holes in lid.
Do not open can.

title: okra - microwave
directions: Drizzle okra with oleo.
Place on plate and cover tightly with Saran Wrap.
(Do not punch holes.)
Microwave for 4 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a skillet, brown sausage; drain. Spray bottom of a casserole dish with nonstick spray.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, soups, milk and poultry in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, lightly greased or sprayed with Pam.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions and spread on top of your mixture.
Bake at 350° until stuffing is done, about 45 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Heat rest of ingredients in saucepan until oleo is melted.
Pour over oatmeal mixture; stir well.
Toast at 275° for 40 to 50 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
In a separate bowl combine eggs, vanilla, coconut and milk.
Butter a large pie plate and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown.
This makes its own crust.

title: gnocchi
directions: Wash, peel and dice potatoes (about 3 1/2 cups).
Steam potatoes until tender, then pass through ricer onto a floured board.
Sprinkle potatoes with salt, then work flour and potatoes until firm (about 5 minutes).
Cut dough into several pieces and roll each piece into a long thin roll (about 1/2 inch in diameter). Cut each roll into tiny pillows.
Dip fork into flour and roll each pillow on the tine of the fork, pressing down with the thumb to make an indentation.
Other side of pillow will have ridges from the fork.
Roll Gnocchi on a floured board.
In large kettle, bring salted water to a rolling boil.
Drop the Gnocchi into the water. When they surface, after a few minutes of boiling, drain and serve with spaghetti sauce, (we call spaghetti sauce sugo) and the Italian grated cheese.
Either Romano or Parmesan will do the trick.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mash bananas; add sugar, nuts and pineapple (drained). Fold in cranberry sauce and whipped cream. Pour in mold or use cup cake papers in muffin pans for showers. Also can be placed in pan to cut in squares and served on lettuce. Freeze.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Beat well with electric mixer. Makes enough frosting for 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour and baking
powder
together; add alternately with milk.
Put 1/2 cup flour on berries; toss gently.
Fold into batter.
Put into a greased tube pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes. Cool. Frost, glaze or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sorghum spice cookies
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs and sorghum. Add flour, soda and spices; mix thoroughly. Chill dough for a few hours or overnight in the refrigerator. Roll into balls the size of walnuts and dip top in sugar. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet (flatten balls somewhat if you prefer a flatter cookie) and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: water chestnut rolls
directions: Wrap strips of bacon around each whole water chestnut and secure the bacon in place with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Clean cabbage, remove core and separate leaves. In a large bowl, mix together ground meat, chopped onions, salt, pepper and uncooked rice. Make into 8 to 10 meatballs.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix in beans, taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Cook until all mixed in.
Then pour cheese on top.
Turn stove on low and let cheese heat on top.

title: oatmeal-apple-raisin muffins
directions: Beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tomato lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Lay flat on foil to cool. Cook onion in oil; don't burn. Add tomatoes, tomato paste and water. Simmer 5 minutes. In bowl, stir together Ricotta, spinach, egg, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan, salt and pepper. In bottom of baking dish, spread 3/4 cup tomato mixture. Spread about 1/3 cup cheese filling on each noodle to within 1-inch of ends. Roll up. Place roll-ups seams down in baking dish. Top with remaining tomatoes. Cover and bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: madhatter meatballs
directions: Blend together water and tomato soup.
Stir in a large pan 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Mix beef, onion, rice and egg.
Make meatballs.
Place uncooked meatballs in pan; cover with a lid and cook for one hour.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake according to directions. While cake is warm, punch holes in cake. Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake. Shake cream of coconut well and pour over cake. Refrigerate cake. Put Cool Whip on top of cake when ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast. Drain. Pull chicken apart. Prepare Stove Top stuffing as directed. In large casserole dish, put Stove Top dressing, soup, Miracle Whip and chicken. Stir well. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook onion and spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add browned pepper, then remainder of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.

title: plum pudding
directions: Break mincemeat into pieces.
Add water and cook slowly, stirring constantly, until all lumps are broken up.
Boil 3 minutes or until liquid is evaporated.
Add coffee and cook mixture.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Pour over fruit and mix.
Put in pan.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to mix in a large rectangular pan.
Let cool about 10 minutes, then poke holes all over it.
Pour condensed milk, then cream of coconut.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix together flour, margarine, and nuts and put into a 9 x 13 dish.
Bake and let cool.
Next mix cool whip, cream cheese and confectionary sugar and spread on cool crust.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together
flour,
baking
powder,	salt and cocoa. Mix together
eggs,
sugar and vanilla.
Melt shortening.
Add flour and
shortening alternately to sugar mixture, until well blended. Pour into
greased	pan.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry orange muffins
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed combining all ingredients. Fill muffin tins and bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes. Makes about 28 muffins.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Mix cream of chicken soup with 1 can of water. Crumble Ritz crackers.
Add cheese, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until onion is cooked.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain rotini.
Slice pepperoni, salami and Provolone into bite-size pieces.
Dice green pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: chili cheese bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in 9-inch square pan.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder. Add melted butter.
Stir in chilies, cottage cheese and Jack cheese.
Mix until blended.
Turn into buttered pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly and cut in squares.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the vinegar, oil and sugar.
Mix and serve.

title: mounds candy bar
directions: Mix coconut, sugar, butter, vanilla and milk together.
Press into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and spread over candy.
Cool and cut into squares.
Keep candy refrigerated.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients and place into a greased casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Make a batter with the first four ingredients.
Then cut the pork into 1 inch cubes and dip into the batter.
Brown in the fat. Cover and cook on low heat for 30 minutes or until tender.
Boil green peppers and then drain.
Add to meat with 1/2 cup pineapple chunks.
Combine and cook 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Then make sauce as follows:

title: blue iceberg wedges
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, Blue cheese, lemon juice, sugar, onion and garlic powder in blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Cover and chill 1 hour before serving.
Core, rinse and drain head lettuce.
Cut into 6 wedges.
Arrange on salad plates with tomatoes and cucumber.
Top with dressing and garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a large bowl, mix spinach, sour cream, onion soup and Cheddar cheese.
Hollow out bread to make a bowl for dip.
Break bread from center into pieces and place around loaf for dipping. Fill hollowed out loaf with dip.

title: granola
directions: Use blender to mix peanut butter and orange juice.
Mix other ingredients well.
Stir in peanut butter mixture; mix well. Spread evenly on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Stir every 5 minutes for even browning.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat until this all blends together and sugar is melted. Especially good on chicken.

title: zucchini delight
directions: In a large bowl, blend the first 10 ingredients.
Add the zucchini.
Pour into a round cake pan.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, pie filling and water.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and saute onion with meat.
Drain off fat. Add taco seasoning and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: garlic potatoes(quick and easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cut each potato into quarters. Place in a 9-inch square microwave-safe baking dish. Combine butter, garlic, parsley, seasoned salt and paprika in a small bowl and mix well. Pour evenly over potatoes. Microwave on High, stirring once, about 10 minutes, until potatoes are tender. Put in the hot oven 6 to 7 minutes, baking until golden brown. Serve with your chicken tenders or grilled steak.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and oleo and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Thoroughly combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs and evaporated milk.
Pour in pan and bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream and refrigerate leftovers.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan stir together all ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes to thicken. Makes 2 cups.

title: millon dollar pickles
directions: Mix cucumber chunks, red peppers, green pepper, onions, salt and drop of alum.
Add water to cover and soak overnight; drain.

title: sausage okra stew
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces and brown in Dutch oven. Saute onion and bell pepper with sausage.
Add tomatoes, soup and okra.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Serve with cornbread and salad.

title: griddle corn cakes
directions: Mix corn meal and boiling water.
Add shortening, molasses and salt.
Then add flour, milk and baking powder.
Bake on hot griddle until firm and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let your sausage be at room temperature when you get ready to mix.
Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
This should make 60 sausage balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken supreme casserole(prepare 1 day ahead.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bring to room temperature and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese straws
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor.
Process until it forms ball.
Chill in refrigerator.
Put between 2 pieces of wax paper and roll out.
Cut into strips.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: liver spread
directions: Saute chicken livers in about 2 tablespoons of margarine until tender (don't overcook).
Season with enough garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste while cooking.
Mash while still quite warm. Mash hard-boiled egg and add to mashed chicken livers.
Moisten with juice from sauteed livers and add dash of Worcestershire sauce, minced onion and about 1 tablespoon of salad dressing for moistness.
Refrigerate about 1/2 hour until ready to serve.
Can also be frozen and kept for 2 days.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, salt and corn oil and boil until soft ball stage.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour into 8-inch square pan.
When set, cut into squares.
Makes 64 (1-inch) squares.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in two layers at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add peanut butter, then 1 cup Cool Whip.
Put mixture into crust.
Top with more Cool Whip.

title: jade salad
directions: Let pineapple boil for 3 minutes.
Add jello and boil 2 more minutes.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese, nuts and whipped cream.
Fold all together and pour into mold.
Chill and serve.
This was always a must for any special occasion.

title: cantaloupe chicken salad
directions: Cook fresh peas in small amount of water 10 to 12 minutes (or place frozen peas in colander and run cold water to thaw). Combine watercress, mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon peel, mustard and pepper. Stir into chicken mixture and chill. Arrange plates with lettuce and arrange cantaloupe slices atop.
Add chicken mixture.

title: curried peaches
directions: Drain peach halves; combine the syrup, sugar, butter and curry powder.
Heat until butter melts, then add peaches.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve warm, topping peaches with sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put catsup in large, heavy cooking pot.
Add chopped onion, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for approximately 2 hours or until thickens down, stirring often.
Then pack in hot jars and hot lids.
Makes about 7 or 8 pints.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust of first 3 items.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine next three items.
Beat at least 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Then layer sliced bananas and cover with the crushed pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over the pineapple.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix well with all ingredients except pecans.
(Use hands to mix.)
Shape into 2 balls and roll in chopped pecans.
Check date on cream cheese and ball will keep until that date or it can be frozen.
Serve with Wheatsworth crackers.

title: chicken lemon oregano
directions: Combine first three ingredients. Put chicken in pan and brush both sides of meat with first 3 ingredients. Sprinkle with oregano leaves. Bake at 350° until done, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hearty hodgepodge
directions: Saute ground chuck, onion and garlic in skillet until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain pan drippings, then pour mixture into a Dutch oven or large pot.
Stir in soup, beans, celery, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Heat oleo in milk until hot and melted.
Beat eggs and add sugar.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Turn on low speed and add vanilla and flour.
Add heated milk and oleo.
Add baking powder and salt.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased and floured pan.
(Makes a good cake for strawberry short cake.)

title: old-fashioned cheese pudding
directions: Butter bread and cut into quarters.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
With cheese as top layer, combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over layers. Cover and bake in 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until knife comes clean.
Serves 6 people.

title: cranberry butter
directions: Bring cranberries and water to a boil in a covered heavy pot. Boil 5 minutes.
Run through a blender and strain into a small heavy pot.
Add juice, rind and sugar and boil for 25 minutes. Strain into a jar and refrigerate.
Delicious on ice cream, yogurt or waffles.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chips, margarine and corn syrup in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 squares.

title: quick fudge
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and cocoa in 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Pour in milk.
Dot with margarine.
Microwave, covered, on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in baking pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions and bake.
While still warm, punch holes in top of cake.
Pour on Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping.
Let cool.
Spread on Cool Whip, then sprinkle on crushed Butterfinger bars.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk together until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Let cool, then pour into a 9-inch baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks; spread over pie.
Lastly, sprinkle coconut over the top.
Brown in the oven at 400° for about 5 minutes.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Saute ground meat until it is browned. Add onion and pepper, stirring until both are slightly cooked. Add the tomatoes (use whole tomatoes which you mash up; it makes it better), salt, pepper, chili powder and water. Cook for a few minutes, then add noodles and cook until the noodles are almost tender. Put half the mixture in a 2 1/2-quart casserole, Pyrex, or flat dish that will hold that amount, that has been sprayed with Pam. Top with cheese. Put remainder of meat mixture in casserole and top with rest of cheese. Bake at 350° until the casserole is thoroughly heated (approximately 25 to 30 minutes) and all the cheese is melted. Serve with green salad and garlic bread or corn bread.

title: graham goodies
directions: Line bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over graham crackers and cook at 375° for exactly 12 minutes.
Remove from pan quickly with a spatula and place on wax paper.
When cool, break pieces apart.

title: liz mitchell's chicken pie
directions: Cook carrots, celery and green beans until tender.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Grease a 12 x 15-inch casserole dish; place chicken in dish.
Sprinkle carrots, celery and green beans over chicken.
Slice the boiled eggs over this.
Mix the cream of chicken soup with broth from the cooked chicken, to make approximately 3 cups.
You may add 1 or 2 bouillon cubes for added flavor.
This may be thickened with 2 or 3 teaspoons of flour. Have this sauce very hot, then pour over the other ingredients. Top with biscuits, made from your favorite recipe.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove chicken.
Skim fat from broth and boil 1 package noodles in broth; drain.
Chop peppers and onions; saute in margarine.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir until dissolved or thawed.
Set in refrigerator 10 minutes.
Pour jello mixture over top of cream cheese.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix cherries and 2 cups sugar together.
In separate bowl mix together ingredients and pour in pan.
Pour juice over batter, then dip cherries on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
When done, cherries will be on bottom and crust on top!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and Ranch dressing mix. Form into two balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: breakfast hot dish
directions: Place croutons in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and mushrooms.
Place browned and drained sausage over croutons. Mix together eggs, milk and soup.
Pour over sausage.
May be refrigerated overnight.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 13-inch oblong pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Reheats well.

title: bud's red potatoes and rosemary
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Slice potatoes into 1/4-inch slices. Melt butter and pour 1/2 of it into large shallow baking pan. Layer potatoes in rows with each slice overlapping the next. Drizzle the remaining butter over all. Sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper and a generous helping of rosemary.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Trim excess fat from beef; heat fat in Dutch oven.
Brown meat slowly on all sides in hot fat.
Add water, sliced onion and seasonings.
Cover and simmer (don't boil), 2 hours, stirring now and then to keep from sticking.
Add vegetables except tomatoes; cook, covered, 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 15 minutes longer or until meat and vegetables are done.
Skim fat from stew. (If you used canned tomatoes, drain; use juice as part of the liquid.)

title: chicken chowder
directions: Combine and cook until tender the chicken, onion, celery tops, bouillon, bay leaf, thyme and water.
Remove chicken, cool and chop.
Strain the liquid, saving the broth.
Saute carrots and celery in margarine until tender in large cooking pot.
Add rice, chicken broth and peas.
Cook until rice is tender.
Add corn, milk and diced chicken.
Season.
Heat and serve.
Serves 10.

title: country beef stew
directions: Heat beef with flour.
Heat oil in heavy, 3-quart saucepan and add beef and onions and brown.
Stir in salt, pepper, soup, evaporated milk and water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth.
This recipe yields 1 1/4 cup, the same as a 14 ounce can.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, but apples.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour batter in pan and place apples on top of batter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain
peas.
Mix all ingredients (being careful not to break sliced eggs).
Chill well before serving.
(Best chilled overnight so flavors can blend.)

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix with spoon.
Drop with teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° for 10 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix clams with juice, 1/2 cup melted butter, 1 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and onion in bowl.
Flatten in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 325° until cheese melts (approximately 15 minutes).
Serve hot with Ritz crackers.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Scald milk in pan.
Add butter.
Cool.
Add sugar, salt, yeast and flour.
Mix well.
Set in warm place to rise.
Work down and let rise again.
Roll out and cut into 2-inch circles.
Let rise again.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.

title: sausage-n-egg casserole
directions: Fry sausage until done, not brown; drain.
Crumble bread in bottom of casserole.
Add sausage, then cheese.
Add milk and salt to beaten eggs; pour in casserole.
Let stand at least 1 hour, or refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Cook beef in skillet until no pink remains.
Add onion.
Saute until tender. Combine beef, onion, ketchup, salt, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar in a 3-quart baking dish.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain and rinse black-eyed peas and hominy and combine.
Add remaining ingredients and Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Marinate overnight.
Serve as a salad on a bed of lettuce or as an appetizer with corn chips.
Serves 8.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except cheese.
Spread cheese on top just before baking.
Bake at 300° in 2 medium (1 1/2-quart) baking dishes (which have been greased) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes two 1 1/2-quart dishes and freezes well.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together.
Chill and serve.

title: date cake
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates.
Add water and mix.
Cream sugar with butter, mix in eggs, salt and flour.
Add to date mixture.
Blend in flavoring and nuts.
If you prefer a less pronounced maple taste use 1 tsp.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 400° for 15 minutes or until cake begins to brown, lower heat to 325° and bake 35 minutes more.
Serve sliced, warm or cold, plain or with whipped cream flavored with lemon extract.

title: sweet potato supper
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with topping.

title: wild rice-sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and cook onion with sausage; drain.
Cook rice according to package instructions.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray muffin pan.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and ginger.
In large bowl, mix carrots, yogurt, egg substitute, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Stir flour mixture into carrot mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately at low speed.
Add vanilla and mace.
Pour in Bundt tube pan.
Cook in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and let stand for 5 minutes before removing from pan. Serves 20 to 22.
Pretty and good.

title: pickled watermelon rind
directions: Day 1:
Use the rind from firm but not overripe watermelon. Trim off the green skin and all pink flesh.
Cut rind into 1-inch cubes.
Measure 2 1/2 quarts and place in large enamel or aluminum canning kettle.
(I find that you can use more than 2 1/2 quarts of watermelon rind.)

title: layered mexican garden salad
directions: On large serving plate, layer lettuce, beans, zucchini, tomato and onion.
Spoon salsa evenly over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
If desired, garnish with red and green chile peppers and cucumber slices.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread cubes; stir well.
Add cheese, mushrooms and sausage.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until firm and gold around the edges.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening in pan.
Add sugar.
Stir only until well mixed.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and chocolate bits.
Pour in greased pan, 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho dip
directions: Take 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon lovers' marmalade
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese from box.
Slice hot dogs and place on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix together raisins, hot water and soda.
Let stand overnight. Mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and butter and add to raisin mix. Add flour and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in slow oven.
Start at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, then down to 275°.
This sometimes takes an extra 10 minutes, depending on your oven.
Check with toothpick, but you don't want it too dry.
Should be slightly moist.
Makes 1 large or two small loaves.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel, core and slice pears.
Place pears in dishpan.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Remove pears from liquid.
Reserve 2 cups of liquid.
Add to pears 5 cups sugar, lemon slices and reserved liquid.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, 1 to 2 hours.
Place in jars and seal.

title: omelet
directions: Coat a dinner plate with margarine.
Shake eggs and water in a jar until blended.
Add to dinner plate.
Cook on High 2 minutes. Stir by pushing cooked areas to center of plate.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes more.
Sprinkle half of omelet with cheese, bacon or whatever.
Put back in microwave for a few seconds until cheese melts.
Remove from microwave.
Turn half the omelet over the other half.

title: chocolate snowflake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oil and melted chocolate in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/4 dry mixture at a time to chocolate mixture and mix each time.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw and drain frozen broccoli; cook rice as directed on package and drain.

Mix into 2-quart casserole dish, broccoli, rice, cream soups, pepper, 1/2 the onions and 1/2 cup cheese. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or 5 minutes in microwave. Top with remaining onions and cheese; bake at 350° for 5 minutes longer or 3 minutes in microwave.
Yield:
About 12 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherry pie filling in a buttered 12 or 13-inch long casserole.
Spread crushed pineapple over this.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Melt oleo and pour over.
On top, sprinkle coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: breakfast toads
directions: Melt butter in pan; add salt and pepper to taste.
Using small glass, cut a hole in slice of bread in center; put in pan.
Crack egg into center of hole.
Fry until bread is toasted on bottom and flip to fry other side.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Roll into small balls and chill. Melt wax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip chilled balls in chocolate and wax mixture.
Use toothpicks to dip balls.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork chops.
Marinate pork chops in sauce every 3 hours in refrigerator.
Place pork chops evenly in a baking dish, pour sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain juice from kraut.
Pour cold water and drain again.
Cut up all vegetables.
Heat sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour all over and mix well.
Refrigerate at least overnight.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: meat casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water for 15 minutes; drain.
Chop pepper and onion.
Cook in small amount of water until tender. Add meat, cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
tags: cream of chicken soup or rice soup

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Knead ingredients (minus butter) for 5 minutes.
Roll and cut into biscuits.
Dip biscuits in butter and bake at 400° for 10 - 15 minutes.

title: quick microwave chicken-potatoes
directions: Cover and place in appropriate size microwave dish; cook and turn until done.

title: mom's orange stuff
directions: In a large bowl mix cottage cheese and dry jello gelatin. Drain mandarin oranges and stir into cottage cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Can be refrigerated for later use or serve immediately.
Cool and delicious.
It's a snap to fix!

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package.
Mix all ingredients in Dream Whip and pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften	and
beat cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and
beat
until
smooth, thick and lemon colored.	Pour into buttered
9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 20 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together; add egg, milk and shortening.
Beat well until smooth, approximately 1 minute.
Bake in greased pan or skillet or muffin pans at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Add crushed wafers, alternating with milk.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Let cool in pan.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: jo's coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and 1 1/3 cups water as directed on cake mix box.
After it cools, punch holes all over cake with a steak knife.

title: old fashioned strawberry jelly
directions: Cover and let boil 1 minute.
Add sugar.
Boil 20 more minutes.
Put into pint jars or jelly jars.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together flour and pineapple juice.
Pat in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread pineapple on crust.
Add Cheddar cheese on top of pineapple.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Very good with ham or chicken.

title: caboose cooler
directions: Combine juice and ale.
To serve, pour over ice cubes and garnish with lemon or orange slices.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar by hand.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Cream until smooth.
Add blueberries; blend well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch buttered pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 45 minutes or until done at 350°.
Remove from oven; brush with butter.
Serve hot or cold. Yields 15 large servings.
May be topped with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Fill skillet with 2 inches of vegetable oil.
Combine all ingredients in bowl and fold in zucchini.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: salmon patties with dill sauce
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
Prepare spinach as label directs; drain.
Arrange spinach on warm platter; keep warm.
In large bowl, combine salmon, eggs, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and 1/8 teaspoon dill weed.
Shape salmon mixture into four 1-inch thick round patties.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook salmon patties 5 minutes or until browned on both sides, turning once.

title: simple fruit cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour and baking powder, use 1/2 flour to dredge fruit.
Mix rest of flour in egg, butter and sugar.
Mix fruit and nuts to frost.
Bake in tube pan. Only takes 30 minutes at 300°, then turn down to 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan, upside down.
Makes 2 small fruit cakes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, then combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and pecans together.
Mix sour cream and sugar and stir into fruit.
Chill.
This makes 4 to 6 servings. (If more fruit is needed, add more pineapple, oranges, grapes and marshmallows.
Also a little more sour cream and sugar.
Chill for at least 6 to 8 hours.)

title: low-fat ice cream
directions: Scald about a quart of milk.
Mix Egg Beaters, sugar and cornstarch and add to scalded milk. Continue to cook until mixture thickens. Cool and add Equal, vanilla and canned milk.
Add enough milk to fill a 1 gallon freezer.
You can make any flavor, banana nut is delicious.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, chilies and onion.
Place in a saucepan over low heat.
Boil and debone chicken.
Heat tortillas in small amount of oil and drain.
(You can heat them in the microwave wrapped in a damp paper towel for less fat.)

title: sugar 'n' spice fruit cup
directions: Place fruit in serving bowl.
Combine the sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle over fruit and toss gently.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine eggs and brown sugar in large bowl, mixing well.
Add fruit cocktail.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Mix butter, sugar, pecans, milk and coconut in saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over warm cake.

title: veggie stuff
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer the vegetables.
Mix the Cheddar cheese according to can directions and pour over vegetables.
Prepare stuffing and layer over top of cheese and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix butter, salt, and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, syrup, and water.
Bring to a
While boiling add peanuts, stirring constantly.
When temperature reaches 300°, remove from heat.
Add butter mixture, stirring briskly.
Pour into desired greased pan.
Cool.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Fold in last can of drained oranges.
Pour into two 8 inch round pans.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool.

title: peach crumb pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell (10-inch deep dish style).
Top with Streusel Crumbs. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together meal, salt and baking powder.
In separate bowl, stir together beaten eggs, corn, sour cream and buttermilk. Combine liquid and dry ingredients and stir well.
Put shortening into an 8-inch iron skillet that you have preheated for a few minutes on top of the stove.
Spoon batter into skillet.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes or until done.
Invert onto a plate and serve.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat flour mixture.
Add melted butter; beat until smooth.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Mix until blended.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk.
Stir by hand 1/2 cup mashed berries.
Add remainder of berries and stir gently.
Line muffin tins with paper liners and fill to the top with batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: fantastic fruit salad
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice together.
Add Cool Whip, pecans, cherries and pineapple and mix thoroughly.
Add marshmallows. Chill overnight.

title: bisquick easy cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Cook beef and onions until brown; drain.
Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with salt and cheese.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: white peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Add peanuts and drop by spoonfuls onto buttered foil.

title: rum chocolate mousse
directions: In the container of a blender, combine first two items with hot scalded milk at high speed.
Add 3 eggs one at a time, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and dark rum.
Pour into six sherbet glasses.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Pat 1 pound hamburger in square cake pan.
Pour mushroom soup over hamburger evenly.
Top with Tater Tots and bake 35 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Takes no effort and tastes like steak.

title: buffalo shrimp with blue cheese dip
directions: Peel and devein shrimp leaving tails intact.
Place shrimp in a shallow dish; cover and chill.

title: instead of salt seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 3 tablespoons.
Contains .33 mg sodium per teaspoon.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix in bowl according to package directions.
Place parchment paper on 15-inch pizza pan (see variations).
Pour brownie mixture on paper; spread into 14-inch circle.
(Do not bake without parchment paper or batter will run off the pizza pan.) Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until set.
Cool to room temperature.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray inside of brown grocery bag with Pam.
Pour popcorn in bag.
In a 2-quart casserole, melt margarine.
Add corn syrup, salt and brown sugar.
Cook at High power; boil for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir until foamy.
Pour mixture over popcorn in bag. Cook bag on High for 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes longer; stir.
Cook another 45 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes.
Spread over cookie sheet to cool.
Store in ziploc plastic bag.

title: chicken celery salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; stir gently.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve salad on lettuce or in stuffed tomato and sprinkle with pecans.
Yields 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Let bread rise.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Pinch pieces of dough and make into ball.
Dip in butter and roll in sugar mixture.
Make 2 layers of balls in Bundt cake pan; pour remaining sugar mixture over top.
Let stand and rise 15 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before eating.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook macaroni until 3/4 done, drain and mix all ingredients together.
Place into greased baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 hour.
Top with more Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese the last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in large deep bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread over the top like icing on a cake.
Let set 12 hours.
Toss well before serving.
At first there does not seem to be enough dressing, but keep mixing and it will be delicious.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix water and cinnamon a little at a time.
Slice apples in casserole dish and pour cinnamon and water over them.
Mix flour, sugar and butter with hands until crumbly and sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry pecan bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In separate bowl mix the remaining ingredients except strawberries and add to dry ingredients.
Stir thoroughly (batter is very thick).
Put some batter on bottom of greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Layer sliced berries; add more batter then more strawberries.
Continue to layer, finishing with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for at least 10 minutes, then turn on rack.

title: veal ragout
directions: Cut veal in cubes; brown in hot pan with small amount of oil. Add vegetables and cook for a few minutes.
Put in casserole dish, cover and cook in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together thoroughly and put in 2 long rolls; wrap tightly in foil, with shiny side toward meat. Refrigerate 24 to 30 hours. Punch holes with fork in bottom only. Place on rack, with pan under. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Lay on foil to cool.

title: butter brickle cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on box. When cake is done, remove from oven and while cake is hot, punch holes in top with fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top and cool completely. When cake is completely cool, frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle butter brickle bits over top.
If unable to find butter brickle bits, crush 2 or 3 Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: heavenly pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, milk, spices and butter in a medium saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool for 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Add pumpkin mix.
Stir to blend completely.
Chill for several hours and serve with whipped cream.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: *Measure oatmeal and blend in a blender to a fine powder.

title: canadian bacon and potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add red pepper and bacon sauteing 1 minute more.
Place potatoes in pot and cook until tender.
Drain.
Mash them and add butter, hot milk, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix until combined.
Stir in onion bacon mixture.
Spoon into casserole dish and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Trim crust from bread; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a heavy skillet heat salad oil and garlic.
Add bread cubes; saute until golden brown and crisp.
Makes 3 cups.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and egg.
Mix flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add to first mixture; add 1 cup molasses.
Stir.
Add hot water last.
Bake in 350° oven until tests done.

title: lazy day pickles
directions: Wash and slice enough cucumbers to fill a gallon glass jar. Add spices (in tied cloth), salt and alum, then cover with cold vinegar.
Let set in dark place for 6 weeks.
Date top of lid when to take out.
At that time, drain off vinegar (do not wash). Layer back into jar with 8 to 10 cups of sugar.
Cloth with 5 spices may be added back to jar.
Let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Leave on pantry shelf.
Take out as many as needed and chill in refrigerator, then serve.
The rest can stay on shelf until used up.
Very crisp.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Cover meat with water.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes, onions and corn to meat stock.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: diet cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with wire whisk.
Place in refrigerate and chill.

title: molded rice and pea salad
directions: Place the rice, peas, scallions, radishes, pepper and cucumber in a large bowl.
Combine the oil, vinegar, garlic and parsley; stir into the rice mixture.
Place the salad in a lightly oiled 2-quart mold, loaf pan or other container.
Pack down lightly and chill for 2 hours.
Invert on a platter to serve.
Serves 4 to 6 as a side dish.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and cook on top of stove until thickened.
Remove from fire and add 2 teaspoons vanilla.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Blend the eggs into pulp.
Sift flour.
Add sugar and spices. Add to pulp alternately with milk.
Fold in raisins; add coconut. Last, blend in the butter.
Pour batter into pan that has been greased and dusted with flour (pan needs to be 2 to 2 1/2 inches deep).
Bake in a 300° oven for about 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken pineapple hawaiian style
directions: Mix together the soy sauce, sugar, vinegar, corn starch; boil for 5 minutes.
Add the pineapple and ginger.
Place chicken in baking pan skin side up, pour boiled mixture over chicken. Bake for 1 hour at 400°. Baste 2 to 3 times if it is convenient. The sauce is excellent over cooked rice.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Mix in blender the eggs, Bisquick and milk.
Mix with hamburg.
Bake in casserole for 20 to 30 minutes (might take longer, depending on your pan size and type).
Add fresh tomatoes (cut in squares or pieces).
Add cheese on top (grated or cubed).

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar and next 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is like coarse meal.
Stir in fruit bits. Add buttermilk and stir until well combined.
Place dough on floured surface and knead for 1 minute.
Form into a ball, place in a greased pie pan and flatten slightly.
With a sharp knife, cut a cross 1/2-inch deep in top of bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: chicken soup
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; wash, then place in pan.
Add 1 onion (whole) and cover with water.
Add salt to taste and water.
Cook for about 1 hour.
In a saucepan, put 3 tablespoons of oil.
When the oil is hot, add cut up tomato, cabbage and remainder of onions.
Add salt to taste.
Fry this mixture approximately 15 minutes.
Add to chicken soup mixture and boil until cabbage is tender.

title: oyster soup
directions: Cook celery in the water until very tender.
Pour into colander and rub through using water and all.
Melt butter.
Add flour and blend together.
Scald milk.
Add and make a white sauce.
Keep hot over hot water.
Put oysters into a saucepan and plump well in their own liquor; remove from fire.
Chop and put through colander.
Add oysters and celery to milk.
Season and serve.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix oil with 3/4 cup warm water. Pour into dry ingredients.
Mix until soft ball.
Add more water if needed.
Cover; allow to rest for 20 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 to 13 small balls.
Roll out each ball on floured surface. Cook on hot ungreased griddle about 1 1/2 minutes per side. Makes 12 to 13 tortillas.

title: oreo cookies cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take out 12 cookies.
Crumble the rest; melt butter.
Pour in pan.
Add crushed cookies and pat flat.
In a bowl, add pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Use mixer until thick.
Pour over crust; stick in refrigerator until cold. Then add Cool Whip on top and crumble the 12 cookies on top. Refrigerate several hours.

title: pollo asado fajitas(barbecue chicken)
directions: Grill chicken until done and dice.
Grill Anaheim chilies, skin and dice.
Slice green pepper.
Slice onion.
Shred cabbage. Stir-fry in hot skillet with the olive oil, garlic, cumin, oregano, salt and pepper.
Serve on flour tortillas with optional ingredients.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Combine 1st four ingredients.
Spoon half the mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 2/3 cup fried onions and 1/2 cup cheese.
Top with remaining potato mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until hot.
Top with remaining onions and cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, until onions are golden.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Place chicken in dish after you've rolled it in crushed Ritz crackers.
You can dip chicken in melted margarine before you roll in crackers if you like.
Bake at 450° until done.
Do not cover.

title: holiday cranberry relish
directions: Grind berries and orange, plus a small amount of the peel, in a food processor.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar, cranberry mixture and nuts.
Let set in refrigerator.
Can be molded.

title: raisin - apple pumpkin pie
directions: Sprinkle raisins in bottom of pie shell.
Add layer of applesauce over the raisins.
In mixing bowl, combine spices, sugar and salt.
Add pumpkin, milk and beaten eggs.
Put mixture over applesauce in the pie shell.
Bake at 400° in lower level of oven 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve with ice cream if desired.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin cups.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; stir in corn meal.
In a medium size bowl, beat eggs just enough to blend yolks and whites. Stir milk and shortening into eggs.
Add dry ingredients; stir to blend, just until smooth.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tasty crackers
directions: Mix until crackers are well coated.
Place on cookie sheet in a 200° oven for an hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: ice cream party pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and corn syrup into large mixing bowl.
Stir until thoroughly combined.
Add frosted cereal.
Mix until well coated.
With the back of the spoon, press mixture evenly and firmly around sides in the bottom of a 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Spoon softened ice cream into the pie crust.
Garnish with semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Freeze until firm.
Yields one pie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, butter and vanilla.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans on top and press down into syrup.
Cook slow at 325° for 1 hour.

title: stanley's spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw and drain spinach.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cook chicken in a large soup pot for about 1 1/2 hours. Remove all skin, fat and bone from chicken and shred meat.
Add shredded meat to broth.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Add water during cooking, if needed.

title: caramel-chocolate squares(serves 28 to 36 squares)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler; set aside.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine dry cake mix, margarine, nuts and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Stir by hand until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough in pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Pour on chocolate chips and caramel.
Spread remaining dough over chocolate chips and caramel layer.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool slightly; refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: basic herb tomato sauce
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes.
Store in clean container and refrigerate.
Use in spaghetti, chili, stew, soups, pizza, etc.

title: lime cheese pie
directions: Place gelatin and hot milk in processor or blender.
Process a few seconds.
Add eggs, sugar, salt and cream cheese.
Process until smooth.
Add limeade and food coloring.

title: new orleans style bread pudding(with bourbon sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In large bowl, combine the bread chunks, milk, and raisins. Mix well. Set aside. Combine the eggs, sugar, and vanilla in another bowl and mix well. Add the bread mixture and mix well. Melt the butter in a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Pour the bread pudding mixture into the pan and bake for 1 hour or until set. Cool and serve with Bourbon Sauce.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in heavy pan.
Reduce heat and add green peppers, onion, kidney beans and tomatoes.
Simmer and add seasonings. Cook 1/2 hour until thick.
Serve with grated Monterey Jack cheese.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole.	Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until top and edges are golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° in a buttered 8 1/2 x 13-inch cookie or cake sheet pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix beef and sausage together with grated onion, bell pepper, egg, salt, pepper and all season.
Form into balls and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Rain and cover with sliced onions, bell pepper and sauce.
Cover and leave overnight.
Heat 45 minutes at 300°.
