title: mushrooms au gratin
directions: *Use paper towels to thoroughly dry.
Button mushrooms preferable or cut larger mushrooms into quarters.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Stir into the sifted ingredients until all the particles of cheese have been separated.
Combine and beat well the egg, milk and butter, lightly stirring from 10 to 20 seconds, which will leave some lumps; ignore them.
Fill well-greased muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at once 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 32 (2-inch) muffins.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, milk and margarine.
Add nuts. Pour in 3 unbaked pie shells.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: saucy stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Remove 8 large outer leaves from cabbage; rinse leaves well. Blanch in boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Shred half of the remaining cabbage to obtain 3 cups.
Set aside.
Reserve remaining cabbage for another use.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, saute onion in butter or margarine for 5 minutes.
Add carrots, celery and rice.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add shredded cabbage and thyme, salt and pepper.
Saute 3 minutes.
Place 1/4 cup of the mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Roll up leaf, tucking in ends to make a bundle.
Place seam side down in skillet; add broth and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Place in serving dish.
Mix 3 tablespoons cold water with cornstarch until smooth.
Stir into liquid in skillet. Stirring over medium heat, bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Pour over cabbage and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: consomme rice
directions: Cut onion fine and brown in margarine in saucepan.
Mix consomme, rice, onion and margarine in casserole dish.
Cover and cook in a 325° oven 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and add other ingredients with cornmeal mix last.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown meat quickly on both sides in heavy pan with cover. Arrange sliced potatoes and onions over meat.
Add seasonings. Pour cream of mushroom soup and milk into pan.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Place bacon and green onion in small bowl; cover.
Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in vinegar, sugar and salt; set aside.

title: winter beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Can be cooked for a full day in large crock-pot.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix chicken, celery, mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice and pepper.
Chill until serving time.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil peppers in boiling water 5 minutes, drain.
Mix rice, onion,
meat
and
cup
cheese.
Generously
stuff peppers with mixture;
top	with
remaining
cup
cheese. Place upright in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until stuffing is hot and topping browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry torte cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slice into 2 layers.
Lay one layer in large bowl (Pyrex is good). Cover with 1/2 of the pudding mix, then add pie filling, then whipped cream with 1/2 of nectar juice.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Add second layer and repeat topping.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust.
Put pie topping on top.
Chill 4 hours.

title: craig claiborne's sauteed mushrooms
directions: Trim off the stems from the mushroom caps.
Reserve both stems and caps.
Rinse the caps and stems in cold water and drain immediately.
Pat dry.
Heat the butter in a skillet large enough to hold the mushroom
pieces in one layer.
Add the mushroom pieces and cook, stirring and shaking the skillet, turning pieces so that they cook evenly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook until nicely browned all over.
They will give up liquid.
Cook until this liquid evaporates.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce, stirring and shaking the skillet.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Toss quickly and serve hot.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and butter together.
Add eggs and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: squash and corn casserole
directions: In double boiler, let squash melt.
Add corn, 1 egg and sugar. Mix and bake in oven and heat (30 minutes or until bubbly, 350° oven).

title: easy cream cheese clouds
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed on electric mixer.

title: ortego pepper bake
directions: Put peppers (veined and seeded) into 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Cover with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Pour egg mixture over peppers.
Grate sharp cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: low cholesterol coffee cake
directions: Spread half of the mixture over one-half of batter that has been placed in greased pan, then the rest of batter and remainder of topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
I double this recipe to fit 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Slowly brown pork in small amount of hot oil.
Add chicken broth and simmer until meat is tender.
Drain pineapple.
Mix juice from pineapple, cornstarch, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Add onion and carrot strips to pork.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add sauce and stir well.
Stir in pineapple chunks.
Serve over hot rice.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Reserve 1 cup Oreos.
Combine remaining crumbs with margarine and press lightly into a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Chill.
Soften cream cheese and mix in powdered sugar. Set aside.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Then add to cream cheese mixture. Spread over crumbs.
Sprinkle with remaining "dirt."

title: chicken salad mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup broth.
Heat remaining broth to boiling.
Stir in softened gelatin until dissolved. Chill until thick and syrupy. Combine with rest of the ingredients.
Stir in whipped cream last.
Pour into 6-cup mold until firm.
Garnish with lettuce and cherry tomatoes.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Chop all vegetables and mix together with Catalina dressing and half the cheese.
Brown meat.
Add salt and taco seasoning. Simmer for 10 min.
Cool, then mix into salad.
Top with chips and remaining cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix broth and soups; heat, stirring, until smooth and hot. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 275° in a 3-quart casserole.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice into large baking dish.
Mix soups, water, salt and pepper together.
Pour over rice.
Put pieces of butter on chicken pieces.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken risotto
directions: Melt small amount of fat in pan.
Fry onion until soft and add bacon.
Add rice and all other ingredients.
Pour on enough chicken stock to easily cover them.
Cook gently until rice is soft and stock has evaporated.
(You may need to add more liquid during cooking until rice is soft.)
Serve hot with green salad.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, if desired.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix and shape into little muffin tins.

title: barbecue chicken basting sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and use beer to baste chicken cooked over coals.
Can also be used for shrimp.

title: instead of tartar sauce for fish
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Serve over fish.

title: charles sykes' peppers stuffed with shrimp
directions: Heat the oil in a pan and gently fry the onion and garlic. Preheat the oven to 350°.
Add the tomatoes, rice, shrimp and coriander to the pan and mix together.
Remove from heat.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, butter and eggs.
Add milk and extract.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggplant puffs
directions: Cook whole eggplant in boiling water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Peel; put the pulp in a bowl.
Drain off any water.
Mash finely with a fork and beat a little.
Add other ingredients except flour and oil.
Beat until well mixed with a whisk or an electric blender.
The final consistency may seem a little thin, but nevertheless, shape into small balls and arrange on a plate.
Let stand in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil until crisp.
Serve hot with toothpicks.
Makes about 24 small puffs.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together in bowl.
Add salt and pepper if you prefer.
Pour this mixture into one pie shell (slightly thawed).	Allow second pie shell to thaw completely. Cover pie with second pie shell.
Press pie shells together at edges and pierce with fork to allow heat to escape.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until desired brownness is reached.
YUM-YUM.

title: conch fritters
directions: Combine the flour, eggs, salt, wine and milk in a blender or bowl.
Beat until butter appears smooth.
Add well drained vegetables.
Batter should not be too thin.
If so, add flour. Deep fry in vegetable oil at 360° until golden brown.
Remove; drain on paper towels.
Taste uncooked batter to see whether it meets your individual specification.

title: sauteed artichokes
directions: Let artichokes thaw.
Melt butter in saucepan and add chopped garlic.
Add artichokes and squeeze lemon juice over them.
Saute, turning frequently, until heated through.
Salt to taste.

title: baby food cake
directions: Measure into
one
bowl.
Mix
thoroughly and add 1 cup chopped
pecans.
Bake
in 9 x 15 x 2 1/2-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let
set 10 minutes; then glaze with the following:

title: southern pound cake
directions: Grease
and
flour
tube pan.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Mix
together
eggs, flour and baking powder.
Add milk and vanilla extract and stir in nuts.
Place in cold oven and set at
Bake
1 hour and 15 minutes. Test cake.
If needed, cool 20
minutes longer.
Don't open door until 1 hour and 15 minutes are up.

title: georgia cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake about 50 minutes at 250°.
Let cool in pan on wire rack, then slice.

title: tomato pie mildred
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice tomatoes.
Fry and crumble bacon. Bake frozen pie shell 5 to 7 minutes.
Place tomato slices in bottom of pie shell.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: apple delight
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in the apples (1/2 cup nuts may be used if desired).
Bake in 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: hawaiian 5 cup salad
directions: Mix and let stand a few hours.
Serve.

title: grapes and pineapple in sour cream
directions: Combine grapes and pineapple.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of brown sugar; blend remaining sugar and the sour cream.
Toss with fruits and chill.
Just before serving, sprinkle with reserved brown sugar.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked spam
directions: Score a whole Spam loaf and dot with cloves.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Baste with mixture of brown sugar, vinegar, prepared mustard and water.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, mayonnaise, garlic and spread on French bread.
Broil about 2 or 3 minutes or until bubbly and starting to brown.

title: great oven chicken
directions: Combine soup mix, dressing and jam.
Mix well (no lumps!). Wash and skin chicken.
Pat dry; overlap chicken in large, flat Pyrex or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, 1 hour, covered and 1 hour, uncovered.

title: angie's fried turkey
directions: Mix together in jar; will cover a few turkeys.
Marinate turkey with these dried ingredients liberally and let sit overnight for best results.
Cook domestic turkey 4 minutes per pound at 350°.
Cook wild turkey 3 minutes per pound at 300°.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and 1 can tomato sauce.
Mix well and set aside.
Cover cabbage leaves with boiling salted water and cook 4 minutes; drain.
Divide meat mixture evenly among cabbage leaves, spooning down center of leaf.
Fold sides of leaf to the center and roll jelly roll fashion.
Place in large skillet, seam down.
Combine tomato sauce with other ingredients; pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover; simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix pie
fillings,
egg
yolks and 1 cup of milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining milk, stirring good.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Pour in baked crust.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 teaspoon of
cream
of
tartar
until thick.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until peaks form.
Spread on pies and bake in a 400° oven until golden brown.

title: oven goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and corn.
Cook and drain egg noodles.
Add noodles and Velveeta cheese to meat mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: chocolate lovers dream
directions: Combine flour, nuts and margarine; press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Next, add paste made of food coloring and cocoa.
Add 1 cup buttermilk with salt, alternately with flour.
Add vanilla and lastly, fold in soda and vinegar.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in oblong pan or 3 (8-inch) layer pans in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: In heavy frying pan, put all ingredients over medium heat. Stir constantly until color of brown butter, about 4 or 5 minutes. Pour quickly in aluminum foil-lined cake pan.
Cool.
Remove foil and break into pieces or leave whole for gift giving.
Makes 3/4 pound.
Be careful when pouring.
It is very hot.
Enjoy.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° F for 45- 50 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off excess liquid.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about one hour.
Serve on hamburger buns or favorite bread or rolls.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Dried fruit can be cut into smaller chunks, if desired.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in large casserole or Dutch oven, covered, at 325° for about 1 hour or until fruit is tender.
Serve hot or cold.
Can be a first course, side dish or dessert (good with pound cake and ice cream).
Keeps in the refrigerator several days.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add and mix together remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate a couple of hours. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Roll into golf-ball size balls.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Leave on tray a little while.
Makes about 112 cookies.

title: milk punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.
It's a delicious dairy treat. Three gallons of ice cream serves 300 people, if you calculate it out.

title: tiger butter
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, break white chocolate up into pieces. Microwave on Medium setting until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Add peanut butter to white chocolate, stirring until melted and smooth.
Melt chocolate chips in another small bowl, stirring frequently, until melted completely.
Line a cookie sheet with wax paper.
Spread the white chocolate-peanut butter mixture evenly over the cookie sheet.
With a spoon, drizzle the melted chocolate chips over the top of the white chocolate.
Refrigerate until firm; break into small pieces.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Good served with ice cream while still warm.

title: raisin buttermilk pie
directions: Place in saucepan in order given, heat until butter is melted. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes, then reduce oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Beat the egg whites with 3 tablespoons sugar, place on top of pie and bake at 325° until brown.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly but well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to zucchini mixture; add nuts.
Bake in two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until tests done. Remove from pans immediately and allow to cool on rack.
Frosting not necessary.

title: veal paprikash(serves 4)
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet. Saute onions until just transparent. Remove from pan and cover.
Fill Dutch oven with water (to cook noodles).
Pound veal until tender; dredge one side in flour and place, flour side down, in skillet.
Turn up heat and saute until lightly browned; turn.
Add sauteed onions to skillet; cover with broth.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Sprinkle paprika until sauce turns red; parsley to taste.
Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and return to heat.
Bring to a slow boil.
Arrange cooked noodles in casserole. Cover with sauce and cutlets.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, together.
Cook bacon and crumble; add to other ingredients.
Toast bread and cut each piece into diagonals (4 pieces) for dipping.

title: snowy apricot bars
directions: Place apricots in 2-quart saucepan; add enough water to cover. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes; drain, chop and reserve.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into granulated sugar and 2 1/2 cups baking mix.
Pat in ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inches).
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Beat brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in apricots, 2/3 cup baking mix, then vanilla and nuts.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Cool completely; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1 inch.
Makes 75 cookies.

title: refrigerator oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Sift together flour and dry ingredients and stir into creamed batter. Add oats and nuts.
Mix well and divide in 3 parts.
Make into rolls.
Wrap rolls in wax paper and chill overnight.
I put them into freezer.
Next day or when you want them, slice 1/2-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: cream tacos
directions: Brown ground beef.
In pot, mix water and brick chili; dissolve.
Add beans, Ro-Tel and ground beef.
Add cheese, cut in pieces, heating all the time.
Melt cheese.
After melted, add whipping cream.
Heat until hot.
Never boil.
Serve over Doritos or plain chips topped with lettuce, onion and tomato.

title: fig conserve
directions: Wash figs and cut in pieces.
Mix with pineapple and lemons. Put into a boiler with an equal amount of sugar and the salt. Bring slowly to boiling point and simmer gently until thickened, but still a little runny.
Stir in nuts; put in hot jars.

title: donna's barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into meatballs and roll each in flour.
Place flour coated meatballs in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Saute pecans in butter on medium-low heat.
After chicken is cooked, coat with mayonnaise and Cool Whip.
Add celery, pecans, chopped fruit and grapes.
Mix well and chill several hours before serving.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind vegetables, sprinkled with 1/2 cup salt with water.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours.
Rinse and drain well.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Pour over vegetables and cook to desired thickness. Put in jars and seal.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Put in dish or large pie plate.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with taco chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour mixture and mix well; then add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube or sheet pan.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly cream together oleo and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Combine flour and egg mixture; add oatmeal, coconut, cereal and nuts and mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake for about 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: quick caramel coffee ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter.
Coat bottom and sides of tube pan.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of nuts over pan.
Add remaining nuts to butter and sugar.
Cut biscuits in half (small balls), the 1/2 nut mixture.
Repeat.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sheri's baked beans
directions: *Plus several pieces for top of casserole.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into shell and freeze.

title: thumbprint tea crisps
directions: Combine ingredients to form large ball.
Make small balls about 3/4-inch diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with thumb.
Place small amount preserves.
Bake at 350° about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dreamsicle pie(sugar free)
directions: Beat cream cheese on high until smooth.
Beat in orange juice, pudding mix and jello.
Stir in half cool whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with remaining cool whip.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
May be used in custard cups without crust.

title: best baked beans
directions: Fry onion and bacon lightly.
Combine all ingredients into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jacqui's cheesecake bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a square 8-inch pan.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add nuts and flour.
Save 3/4 cup of this mixture.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan for crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper towels to remove moisture. Press hash browns on bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie pan to form a crust.
Drizzle melted butter over crust.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Toss together the ham and cheese and place in crust. Beat the cream with the eggs and seasoned salt.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Bake, uncovered in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: loose pack frozen hash brown potatoes

title: ethan's favorite candy
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until it is mixed up well (you may need to use your hands).
Roll out on waxed paper to about 1/4 inch thick.
Spread peanut butter on top of cream cheese mixture.
Roll up into a log.
Place in refrigerator for about 1 hour and then slice into 1/2 inch pieces.

title: sweet sour green beans
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Wrap in paper towel and set aside. Brown the minced onion in the bacon fat and add flour.
In a large saucepan, heat the bean liquid until boils.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in the green beans.
Pour into serving dish and sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.
Serve.

title: chafing dish hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except last 2.
Form into tiny balls 1/2-inch in diameter.
Flatten slightly to resemble hamburgers. Roll lightly in flour.
Fry in hot fat.
Place in chafing dish and mix with warm barbecue sauce.
Serve with miniature buns.
Makes 25 to 30.

title: tropical glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Arrange slices so edges overlap in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup syrup; set pineapple aside.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except popcorn and soda in a microwave-safe dish.
Boil 2 minutes on High.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Pour syrup over corn in a brown paper bag.
Shake. Microwave on High 1/2 minute; shake.
Repeat.
May need to repeat a third time.
Pour out onto a cookie sheet to cool.

title: quick appetizers
directions: Take 2 slices of beef and lay out flat.
Spread cream cheese on beef.
Take 1 green onion and roll it up in the beef.
Serve cold.

title: hamburger for tacos
directions: Simmer all for at least 15 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in an airtight container. For each mug of hot cocoa, put 1/3 cup mixture into mug.
Add hot water and stir.
Use more or less to taste.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Mix ingredients together in a saucepan or in fondue pot.
Heat gradually, stirring occasionally.
Fills one fondue pot.
Great for dipping bread and cooked vegetables in.

title: pineapple glaze cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on the label.
Bring to boil the pineapple and sugar.
With point of sharp knife, mark warm cake in 1 inch squares, cutting 1/2 inch deep.
Spoon hot pineapple mixture over cake.
Cool.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy potatoes o'brien
directions: Mix potatoes and cheese.
Mix soup, sour cream and milk.
Add to potatoes.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave yams-hawaiian style
directions: Combine yams, pineapple, pineapple juice, butter, sugar and cinnamon in a 3-quart casserole.
Beat until creamy and well-blended with portable mixer or by hand.
Fold in pecans. Sprinkle with brown sugar and drizzle with butter.
Cook in microwave for 7 to 10 minutes, giving dish a 1/4 turn once during cooking time.

title: sugar shortbread yums
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine butter and sugar; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup. Level off. Stir in flour, mixing well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.

title: summer pudding
directions: *Use fruits such as raspberries, red currants, black currants, blueberries or blackberries (use a mixture, or all one fruit).

title: yardstick
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients as for pie.
Add water, yeast and eggs.
Mix well.
Divide in 4.
Roll into rectangle.
Cream 1 stick butter, 1 cup sugar and almond extract.
Spread over 2/3 of rectangle.
Fold an prick.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: party chicken
directions: Line a 2-quart greased baking dish with dried beef. Wrap each chicken breast with bacon.
Place on dried beef.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serve with wild rice.

title: "frog's" shrimp scampi for two
directions: Melt butter and oil.
Add garlic powder and parsley flakes. When it starts to boil, add a shot of wine.
Mix, then add the precooked shrimp.
Heat up about 1 minute.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add the milk, sugar and topping.
Mix well.
Pour into shells and freeze.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Cream the butter and both sugars
until
fluffy.
Add egg and beat thoroughly. Mix in
water
and	vanilla.
Stir	together
flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add
to
egg
mixture
and mix well. Add oats and raisins and
mix.
Form giant cookies and bake 15 to 17 minutes until edges are done but centers are still soft. Remove to a rack to cool.
Makes 25 to 30 large cookies.

title: chicken saute
directions: Cut chicken in slices
or
small chunks.
Dip in melted butter; roll in bread crumbs.
Saute in remaining butter until golden brown on both
sides
(this	doesn't take long).
Serve hot with cocktail picks.

title: "sister lint" banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 3 (2 pound) coffee cans. Pour mix into them.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Now you can freeze in cans and use later.
You can use 3 small loaf pans if you prefer.

title: vallie's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating as you add.
Add other ingredients alternately.
Mix and beat about 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake, starting in cold oven, at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and cup of water thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to jell.
In a small bowl, stir and mash cranberry sauce until smooth, add to gelatin.
Then add apples, pineapple, pecans, lemon juice and salt.
Leave in refrigerator overnight for best results.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat until chicken is done. Serve over cooked pasta.

title: donna rustand's golden carrot bake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in onion, salt and pepper. Pour mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
In large saucepan melt margarine and add brown sugar.
Cool slightly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut when cool into squares.

title: peanut bars
directions: Melt butter and chips in microwave.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix in 2 cups marshmallows.
Put half of the dry roasted peanuts in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixture over peanuts.
Add rest of peanuts on top.
Press down and cool; refrigerate.

title: ravioli with ratatouille(meatless)
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven or large saucepan over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except for ravioli.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Cook uncovered an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all filling ingredients and chill for 24 hours.
Spread filling evenly over tortilla shells.
Roll up and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Slice into 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick slices.
Discard end pieces.
Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Mix salad dressing and evaporated milk.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers and stir to mix well.
Is better if made ahead of time.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix 1/2 c. sugar and cinnamon. Roll biscuit pieces in sugar mixture and put in a greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter, remaining sugar and vanilla until sugar is completely dissolved.
Add pecans and pour over biscuits.
Cook at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 3 minutes then turn out of pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until transparent.
Add all other ingredients except meat or poultry.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add meat and simmer until heated through.

title: top of the stove fudge cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and peanut butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil for at least 2 minutes.
Mix well with cocoa, oatmeal and oat bran in a mixing bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: four fruit jam
directions: Mash fruits well;
add sugar.
Bring to boil and simmer 40 minutes.
Stir often while simmering; can easily burn.
Add jello and heat well and can.

title: festive carrot cake
directions: Beat
sugar and eggs with mixer until light and fluffy. Then add
cooking
oil
and
beat 2 minutes more.
Add rest in order given.
Bake
in
350° oven for 45 minutes or until done in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: bourbon walnut pound cake
directions: Mix nuts and bourbon.
Let stand.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter with sugar until light.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat at high speed, occasionally scraping sides of bowl with rubber scraper, for 4 minutes until mixture is thick and fluffy.
At low speed, gradually mix in flour mixture until just combined.
Stir in bourbon and walnuts.
Turn batter into a 10-inch tube pan which has been well buttered and floured.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Soak cheesecloth in 1/2 cup bourbon.
Wrap cake completely in cheesecloth, then in foil.
Refrigerate for several days.
Slice thinly.
A large slice will not only spoil it, but kill you!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large bowl; blend well.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Do not beat.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 lightly greased small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Flour and brown chops on both sides.
Place in single layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 4 or 5 apples, cored and sliced. Mix together and sprinkle over top the brown sugar, raisins, salt, pepper and sage.
Mix the hot water and vinegar; pour over all. Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp cankton salad
directions: In large stockpot, bring 4 quarts water to a rolling boil over high heat.
Add shrimp.

Shrimp will almost immediately turn pink. Let water return to a boil (use a wooden spoon to gently stir shrimp to let water reheat more quickly), then immediately remove pot from heat and use tongs to remove one shrimp.
Test for doneness by shelling and eating; this is lagniappe!
(Do not overcook.
The shrimp are almost ready to eat when they first turn that lovely pink color and are opaque.)
If shrimp are not cooked, return pan to high heat and cook a few seconds more, just until done.
Immediately pour them into a colander (reserve liquid to use as shrimp or seafood stock in other recipes) and run cold water over shrimp or place a few ice cubes on them to cool them for shelling.
Shell and devein shrimp and reserve.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Use 1 rounded teaspoon of mix to 1 cup of hot water.

title: mushroom-rice casserole
directions: In skillet, saute celery, onion, green pepper and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes longer.

title: brussels sprouts soup
directions: Boil sprouts in about 1 cup of water until tender.
Cool and cut.
Put flour and butter in double boiler and stir with a wire whisk until smooth. Gradually add water from sprouts and dissolved bouillon.
Stir constantly.
Add sprouts.

title: butter mints
directions: Scald 1/4 cup of whipping cream.
Melt 1 stick (1/2 cup) butter.
Add 1 teaspoon mint flavoring and 1 teaspoon butter flavoring to melted butter.
Add food coloring of choice and intensity to butter mixture.
Add scalded whipping cream to 1 box powdered sugar.
Mix together, using your hands to knead into ball stage.
Add butter mixture to powdered sugar mixture.
Mix well. If necessary, add more sugar until mixture is well formed. Separate mixture into smaller balls and roll out into long strings.
Cut with a knife and place on a dish to air dry for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Place in tightly sealed container.

title: deviled crab bites
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in bowl; stir well.
Add crabmeat, crumbs and green onions; stir well.
Spoon 1 teaspoon crabmeat mixture onto each cucumber slice; sprinkle with paprika.

title: instant salad
directions: Drain fruit; add 1 cup of the juice in the pudding and mix; add peaches, pineapple and bananas and chill.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter; mix in flour and brown sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks; stir well.
Add water gradually.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla and cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites, powdered sugar and baking powder until stiff peaks forms.
Cover pie with meringue.
Bake in 350° oven until meringue is golden brown.

title: frozen caramel pie
directions: Melt butter, add coconut and nuts.
Cook until golden brown.

title: hearty soup and blt salad
directions: In medium skillet, fry bacon over low heat until crisp. Remove with slotted spoon and drain completely on paper towels. In small bowl, beat together oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper; set aside.
Place lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and bacon in salad bowl.
Pour on dressing and toss gently.
Prepare soup according to package directions.
Remove to serving bowls and serve with salad.
Serves 4.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Select fresh cucumbers.
Wash and cut into sticks.
Pour boiling water over the sticks and let stand 12 to 14 hours or overnight.
Drain and pack into clean jars.

title: meatballs with pinto beans
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Drop into pinto beans and cook until meatballs are done and liquid is thickened.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook in saucepan the Velveeta, mayo, butter and soup until blended.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan coated with Pam, layer 1/2 rice, 1/2 broccoli and 1/2 cheese sauce.
Then add rest of rice, all of chicken and on top of this the rest of broccoli and the rest of the cheese sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Grease crock-pot with margarine. Mix all ingredients and pour in crock-pot. Cut several thick slices of medium cheese on top. Cook for 3 hours on low. Stir often.

title: tate's own busy day vegetable soup
directions: Combine in a large, heavy pot; cook over medium heat, covered, until barley and meat are tender.
If using stew meat, cook meat about 40 minutes before adding rest of ingredients.
Delicious served with warm, buttered bread and fruit!

title: spicy pecan pork
directions: May substitute veal for the pork loin.

title: goo goo
directions: Mix all together using Jell-O dry.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until thick.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets; add chopped onion, raisins and sunflower seeds; stir.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Wash and pat dry the meat.
Put it in a high, not very wide, bowl.
Pour in enough vinegar to just cover the meat.
Add bay leaves and black peppercorns; let marinate, covered, in the refrigerator for approximately 2 days.
Turn the meat at least once.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of pie, if desired, before baking.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix well, then add 2 cups Cool Whip; mix well.
Place in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate before serving.
This freezes well. Enough to make 2 pies.

title: spanish frittata
directions: Cut potatoes, onion, zucchini and green pepper into medium dice.
Using medium-high heat, in a nonstick 10-inch skillet, saute potatoes, onion, zucchini and green pepper in 2 tablespoons olive oil until lightly browned.
Reduce heat to medium and add 3 eggs that have been beaten with 3 tablespoons of water, salt and pepper.

title: 4-h barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off excess fat.
Chop onions.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bake in roaster at 200° for 1 hour.

title: mother's chicken casserole with wild rice
directions: Place chicken in a deep kettle.
Add water, sherry, salt, curry powder, onion and celery.
Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer 1 hour.
Remove from heat.
Refrigerate chicken and broth separately.
When chicken is cool, remove meat from bones, discard skin.
Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Wash mushrooms and saute in butter until golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour and sugar and set aside.
Put in saucepan and bring to boil, oleo, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and mix well (don't wash out saucepan).
Add vanilla, baking soda, buttermilk and eggs.
Grease and flour 18 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir in onions, salt and pepper.
Add milk if too dry.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Use 13 x 8-inch glass dish.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup very cold water.
Drain blueberries and add to Jell-O.
(Blueberry pie filling will work also).
Add nuts and refrigerate.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Spread over firm Jell-O.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Note:
Two cups water and 1 cup raw rice equals 2 cups cooked rice.

title: cannoli pastries
directions: Prepare Cannoli Pastry Shells; set aside.

title: whipped honey butter
directions: In
small
mixer bowl, on medium speed, mix ingredients until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on hot biscuits, muffins and pancakes.
(Great on cornbread.)

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato with jacket on until done.	Remove peeling, mash and mix with half of powdered sugar.
Add cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Mix with fingers until of doughy consistency by adding most of the remaining sugar.
Place mixture on wax paper which has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll out flat to a 1/4-inch thickness oblong shape.
Spread peanut butter over surface and roll up as a jelly roll.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Slice and serve.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Pour barbecue sauce over chicken
after placing it in a 14-inch Dutch oven.
Add Pepsi.
Bake
covered
for
1 hour on medium heat.

title: grandma wilson's cereal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, vegetable oil, vanilla, brown sugar and eggs.
Then add flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, salt, crushed cereal and nuts.
(Dough will be very stiff!)

title: homemade pizza crust
directions: Soften dry yeast in the warm water.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups flour, oil and salt.
Stir in 2 more cups flour and knead until smooth and elastic, about 12 minutes (will be firm).
Place in a lightly greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover, let rise in a warm place until doubled (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Punch down, cover and chill.
Cut dough in half.
On lightly floured surface, roll each into a 12-inch circle about 1/8-inch thick.
Place in 2 greased 12-inch pizza pans.
Crimp edges.
Brush each circle with 1 tablespoon oil.
Fill with desired toppings.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: almond bark treats
directions: Melt 2 (24 ounce) packages almond bark on low heat for 2 minutes.
Stir until melted.
Pour slowly over mixture.
Mix well. Spread on wax paper.
Let cool; break apart.

title: chili con carne for 60 men(war department document, dated 1910)
directions: Chop meat into 1/2-inch cubes.
Fry in the same manner as beef steak, but use a smaller amount of fat.
Cover fried meat with about 1-inch of beef stock.
Add ground chilies, chili powder and salt to taste.
Run 2/3 of boiled beans through a meat chopper and stir into meat mixture.
Add remaining third or beans whole. While cooking, it may be necessary to add more beef stock to replace that lost be evaporation.
Simmer for 1 hour or more until meat is tender and mixture is proper consistency.
When ready to serve, there should be sufficient liquid to cover the preparation.

title: twisty pretzels
directions: Put yeast into a bowl.
Add flour, sugar, warm water and salt. Mix the dough together until it makes a ball.
Put some flour on your hands and sprinkle a little on a board or table.
Knead the dough until it is smooth.
Punch it and squeeze it until it feels like a rubber ball.
Break off pieces of dough the size of a walnut.
Roll each piece into a long string.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and cranberry sauce in the hot water.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour 2 cups of mixture into a clear glass bowl. (Spray first with Pam.)
Chill Jell-O until firm.
(Leave rest of mixture set out until ready to use.)
When first mixture is jelled firm, add a layer of whipped sour cream.
Then pour rest of mixture over top of sour cream layer.
Chill until firm.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Bake pie shells according to directions.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour into baked, cool pie shells.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: peach pie
directions: Whip condensed milk and lemonade.
Prepare topping mix according to directions on package.
Line pastry shell with peaches.
Fold milk and lemonade into whipped topping and pour over peaches.
Chill.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine first four ingredients; mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Chill 1 hour.
In double boiler, melt chocolate and paraffin.
Remove from heat but allow to remain over hot water. Using fork, dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to harden.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Add dry ingredients to moist.
Dough will be runny.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes (15 bigger).

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix well:
peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Shape into eggs. Cool in refrigerator.
In double boiler, melt the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip eggs in chocolate.

title: bonbons
directions: Cream oleo and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix by hand.
Make into balls. Chill (overnight best).
Melt 12 ounces chocolate chips and 3/4 bar of paraffin.
Dip balls and place on waxed paper.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add other things.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: perfect iced tea
directions: Bring water to boil; remove from heat.
Add tea bags and steep for 5 minutes.
Add sugar to the hot tea.
Dissolve it good.

title: bahamian pork chops
directions: Sear seasoned chops in butter or oil.
Place in large casserole.
Saute bacon in skillet until partially cooked.
In bacon grease, saute sliced onion, peppers and garlic until limp. Add ginger.
Remove from skillet.
Stir celery soup and water in skillet until blended.
Put bacon and vegetables over chops.
Pour soup over mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except for the butter.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Pour butter over the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Coat tube pan heavily with Crisco.
(I always line my tube pan with wax paper on bottom, cut to fit.) Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: biscuit mix brownies
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and butter in a microwave-safe bowl; microwave at High 2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in condensed milk and next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly on a wire rack.
Spread chocolate frosting on warm brownies, if desired. Cut into squares.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Beat the softened cream cheese.
Mix Jell-O according to directions and add to the cream cheese.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple and mix.
Pour into a mold or a fancy glass bowl.
This makes a pretty salad.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, covered. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into a loaf.
Place in a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy tapioca pudding
directions: Stir first 5
ingredients constantly while cooking. Bring to a full boil.
When cool, mix in 1 cup pineapple.
Before serving, add package of
Dream Whip, whipped.
Save some for decorating and top with cherries.

title: stirred steak and vegetables(microwave)
directions: Place meat in a 2 1/2 quart, covered, glass casserole dish. Cook on Roast for 4 to 5 minutes until meat is no longer pink; stir occasionally.
Top beef with sliced vegetables.
Combine tomato sauce, soy sauce, vinegar, garlic and ginger to sauce. Pour over vegetables.
Cover and cook on Roast for 5 to 6 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Arrange vegetables in center of platter.
Ring with meat and top with sauce.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and flavoring; blend well.
Add mixture to flour.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-15 minutes.

title: beef burgers
directions: Brown ground beef in oil until crumbly, not hard.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer slowly 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve on toasted buns.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Mix ham and butter.
Make biscuits with recipe of one's choice. Bake biscuits and cool.
Fill with filling (ham).
The biscuits can be prepared in advance and warmed in oven or microwave before serving.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Cut up the lettuce.
Place into a 9
x 3-inch dish.
Sprinkle the next 4 ingredients over lettuce in layers.
Spread mayonnaise over peas. Sprinkle next 4 ingredients over mayonnaise in order. Cover and chill. Can be made the day ahead.
Keeps well.

title: "lorallie's" lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic and olive oil.
Mix tomato sauce, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
In bottom of greased baking dish, spoon in 1/2 of meat sauce, 1/2 lasagna, 1/2 pizza cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Form another layer of remainder of lasagna, pizza cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella. Top with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with remainder of Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: In skillet, saute onion in butter until soft; add ground meat. In buttered pan, layer carrots on 1/2 cabbage; add meat mixture. Press down slightly; add remaining cabbage to spaghetti sauce and chives.
Pour on top of casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour until cabbage is soft.
Add cheese on top.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes until the cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: basic french salad dressing
directions: Shake to blend and store in jar in refrigerator.
Serve on salad greens or use as a marinade for vegetables, fish or chicken.

title: fruit and ice cream pie
directions: Drain strawberries and reserve 1/4 cup syrup.
Stir strawberries into 3/4 cup of the jam.
Drop tablespoons of strawberry mixture and heaping soup spoonfuls softened ice cream alternately into pie crust.
Smooth surface with spatula, mounding filling slightly in center.
Cover with plastic lid and freeze at least 4 hours until firm, or up to 1 week.

title: sweet pickle rings or strips
directions: Put cinnamon and cloves in bag or cloth.
Place in with pickles, juice and sugar.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box except use milk instead of water. Bake in regular cake pan.
Cut in two layers with thread (best done when cake is warm).

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Layer ingredients as follows in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish: soup, tortillas, soup, peppers, onions, chicken, cheese, tortillas, soup and cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together except vinegar.
Gradually add vinegar and mix well.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Melt the chocolate. When cool, stir into the sugar mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at high speed for 5 minutes after each addition.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill for about 2 hours until firm or can be frozen.

title: liverwurst pate
directions: Let cream cheese and liverwurst warm to room temperature in mixing bowl.
Saute mushrooms in butter until lightly brown. While warm, add all ingredients to cheese and liverwurst.
Mix thoroughly and put into containers and refrigerate.
Will keep weeks or can freeze.

title: cajun lamburgers(serves four)
directions: Chop small green onions and green olives.
Place in a 2-quart mixing bowl.
Add ground lamb.
Crush garlic clove and add to mixture.
Add eggs, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, Louisiana hot sauce and a dash of black pepper; mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended.
More bread crumbs can be added if mixture is too moist and sticks to your hands.
Make meat into patties of desired size.
Cook on grill until desired doneness.
Serve with Cajun Ketchup, if desired.

title: country butter
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl; mix with electric mixer until thick.
Keep refrigerated.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Grease glass 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with butter.
Put cooked rice in dish.
Add cooked broccoli to next layer.
Add precooked shrimp and cover with cheese.
Pour salad dressing over cheese.
(Use 1/2 to 3/4 of the dressing.)
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: date nut bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt and add to butter mixture alternately between flour and water.
Add nuts and dates.
Blend well.
Pour into a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kraut salad or relish
directions: Mix all together and let stand for 24 hours before serving.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Melt chips and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in crushed crackers.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture.
Press remaining mixture in ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cherry chocolate kisses
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat butter in bowl for 30 seconds.
Add powdered sugar and salt.
Beat in cherry liquid and almond extract until blended.

Beat in as much flour as you can with a mixer. Stir in remaining flour and the chopped cherries with spoon. Shape dough into one inch balls, 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten to 1/2 inch thickness with the bottom of a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake about 14 minutes.
Remove from oven and press a chocolate Kiss into each cookie.
Cool. Makes 48 cookies.

title: easy sauerkraut supper
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion; cook, stirring often, 3 minutes.
Add sauerkraut, wine, apple, brown sugar and caraway seed; mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes or until tender.
Add sausage or franks and cook 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: melting moments
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour, cornstarch and powdered sugar.
In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat butter or margarine until smooth.
Add flour mixture and vanilla; beat until well blended.
If necessary, refrigerate until easy to handle.

title: cafe au lait
directions: Combine milk, coffee and Hot Buttered Drink Mix in a mug and stir well.
Garnish with dollop of whipped cream and sprinkle with chocolate if desired.
Give mixture of Hot Buttered Drink Mix recipe and mugs in a decorated basket to someone you care about.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 3/4 cups boiling water.
Slice bananas; mix all ingredients together except the Cool Whip.
Pour half in a casserole dish.
Let congeal, then spread Cool Whip over this layer.
The other half of jello mixture should be cooling in the refrigerator while layering the first part.
After spreading Cool Whip in dish, place second half of jello over it.
Salad contains 3 layers.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk, lime juice, lemon juice and food coloring.
This mixture will thicken.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold into mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with whipped cream or candy gumdrop flowers.

title: lemon herb chicken
directions: In large shallow baking dish, mix lemon juice, corn oil, parsley, dill weed, salt and pepper.
Add chicken; turn to coat. Cover; refrigerate, turning occasionally, several hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Grill or broil 6 inches from heat, turning and brushing frequently with marinade, 35 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: uncle willie's barbecue sauce(west tennessee style)
directions: Cook for 45 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add about 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend in.
Take out lemons before adding sugar.
Add touch of cloves, cinnamon and cream of tartar.
Cook 15 minutes more.

title: christmas caramels
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir in corn syrup. Gradually add condensed milk.
Stir constantly over medium heat until it reaches a firm ball stage (245°).
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into well buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool, cut and wrap.
Makes about 50 caramels.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: apricot cake
directions: Set oven at temperature for cake mix.
Pure can of apricots with juice.
Combine eggs, pure and cake mix.
Beat 2 minutes until mixed.
Pour into greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake according to mix.
Cool 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle heated jam over cake while warm.

title: pancake house pancake
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
After 2 weeks, add a tablespoon of sugar.
Will keep for a month.

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Skin eggplant; cut into 1/2-inch circles.
Beat eggs; dip eggplant into eggs, then bread crumbs.
Brown in oil; drain on paper towels.
In baking dish, layer sauce first; eggplant; sauce; sprinkle with grated cheese, then Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat until all eggplant is used.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until hot and cheese is melted.

title: ref. frozen pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt on cut onions and mix.
Let set 2 hours.
Heat vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Cool.
Add to cucumbers.
After 2 to 3 days in refrigerator, they have to be frozen.

title: rump roast
directions: Season and flour roast. Brown on both sides. Pour grease off and put back in skillet. Add water. Cover with foil. Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours in oven at 300° to 350°. Take out and slice thin. Put roast back in skillet and add mushroom soup. Cover with foil and cook for an additional 30 minutes.

title: south of the border supper
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare chili as directed using beef, water, tomatoes and beans.
In medium bowl, beat together egg, milk and oil.
In a small bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, potato flakes, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Spoon chili mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Drop corn bread mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot chili.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine, butter and sugars. Add egg and mix well.
Add oil, oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts; stir well.
Add flour, soda and salt mixture.
Form into balls the size of walnuts and flatten with a fork dipped in water. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: esther's dip
directions: Chop peppers, onions and dried beef.
Mix all ingredients together, using enough Miracle Whip to make creamy.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Put eggs, shortening and milk in bowl.
Add the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat with a spoon until mixed.
Pour out on board and work with hands until dough is smooth.
Roll out and cut.
Fill with fresh fruit filling or canned fruit filling, fold over, seal and fry in hot oil until golden.
I make my pies the size of a saucer and this will make about 20 pies.

title: curried zucchini soup
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in 3 tablespoons butter until soft. Add stock. Cook for 20 minutes. Slice unpeeled tomatoes and saute in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add to other mixture and bring to a boil. Mix flour, water, curry and spices.
Add to soup.
Cook 6 minutes.
Run through blender.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding carrots last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham tea biscuits
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise through center.
Put a slice of ham and cheese in each tea biscuit.
Replace tea biscuits into thin tray. Melt margarine and other items together.
Pour this over tea biscuits and allow to set.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: beef broth
directions: Broth:
Peel and cut carrots and onions into quarters.
Chop celery (include tops).
Heat oil in large soup pot.
Dredge meat in flour.
Brown on both sides in oil.
Add carrots, celery and onions.
Add water to cover.
Salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce to slow boil for approximately 1 hour.

title: greek rice pudding
directions: Put milk on to boil.
Wash rice and add to the milk.
When it comes to a boil again, reduce heat and simmer for about a half hour, stirring occasionally.
Add sugar, lemon rind and egg yolk mixture.
Simmer a few minutes longer.
Serve on dessert plates, when cold.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: pumpkin squares(very good)
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy.
Stir in the rest.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Add salt to tomatoes and onions and let stand overnight. Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour until very thick.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 16 pints.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add baking powder to flour and add alternating with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in flavoring and coconut. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease and flour one large or two small loaf pans.
In large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar; add the eggs.
Blend well.
Add the bananas, flour, baking soda, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan/pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: cranberry oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat together well. Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well. Stir in oats, cranberries and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes if chewy cookies or 12 to 13 minutes for crispy cookies.
Cool. Yield:
approximately 5 dozen.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all filling ingredients and pour into pastry shell. Bake at 300° for 1 hour 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 pie.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together	sugar,	flour, salt and margarine.
Add eggs (one at
a	time), buttermilk and lemon extract.
Cook in unbaked pie shell at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in the order given; form dough about the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix thoroughly in saucepan the brown sugar and flour. Add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 15 minutes. Separate the eggs.
Beat whites to soft peak stage, then beat yolks to break up.

Stir about 1/2 cup cooked mixture into yolks, then stir yolks into mixture. Stir whites into mixture. Add vanilla, if desired. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until it bubbles, about 5 minutes.
Line bottom of an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex with graham crackers, broken to bite size.
Pour half the custard on top of crackers.
Slice 2 bananas onto mixture, then pour remaining custard.
Add another sliced banana on top, if desired.
Refrigerate.
Vanilla wafers may be substituted for crackers.

title: quick cake
directions: In saucepan, mix water and margarine; bring to boil.
In bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Pour saucepan mixture into bowl; mix well.
Beat eggs in buttermilk; add to mixture, mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes. Cut up or mash them. Add mayonnaise and cheese. Mix well and heat at 350° until bubbly. Do NOT cook. Can be heated in microwave.

title: cape sante alla veneziana
directions: Stir-fry scallops in olive oil; season with salt and pepper. Butter a small baking dish and transfer scallops.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix bread crumbs, garlic and parsley and sprinkle over scallops.
Baste generously with melted butter and broil 4 inches from broiler until crumbs turn golden.
Serve with lemon wedges (six portions).

title: mission inn potatoes
directions: Bring 1 cup water to boil in saucepan; add potatoes, onion, garlic, salt and bouillon.
Return to boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and cook, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Pour half of the potatoes into shallow casserole dish, greased.
Cover with half the cheese and chilies.
Top with remaining potatoes, cheese and chilies.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Spread mixture of egg and sour cream over top; sprinkle with paprika. Bake 10 minutes or until golden.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Heat oil; spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Roll sliced tomatoes in corn meal; add to heated oil.
Salt to taste.
Add light dash of garlic powder to each slice.
Cook until brown.

title: mom's pancakes
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Beat eggs lightly; stir in milk.
Then add melted shortening and all liquids to flour mixture; beat mixture until smooth.
Bake on hot griddle until golden brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Layer One: Cover bottom of trifle bowl with pieces of cake.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Grate or grind the four vegetables.
Drain well.
Add mayonnaise to cream cheese and mix well.
Add drained vegetables. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna-noodle bake
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender, drain.
In saucepan add mushroom soup.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk; stir until smooth.
Drain tuna.
Mix macaroni, tuna fish and mushroom soup.
Turn all ingredients into casserole dish.
Cover mixture with shredded cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set and cheese melts.
Serve.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add butter, milk, eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, pineapple juice and sugar in a gallon container and finish filling with water.
Add ginger ale when serving. Store in refrigerator.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Decorate punch as desired. Yields 70 servings.

title: basic dinner rolls
directions: Cream together yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and eggs until liquid.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, salt, water and butter.
Add flour. Beat well by hand.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small pieces (takes about 2 months).
Put in large kettle.
Cook for 2 weeks at 465°.
Thicken broth for gravy. Serves about 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, add 2 rabbits, but this should only be done in an emergency, as most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: gary's breakfast
directions: Chop bacon into small bits and fry in skillet.
Drain grease; add onions and peppers and cook until soft.
Add corn.
Mix eggs. After eggs are beaten, add to skillet to fix as scrambled eggs. Scramble to taste and serve hot with toast or bread.

title: onion soup au gratin
directions: Saute onions in melted butter until soft.
Blend in flour and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth, salt and cayenne.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Lower heat; simmer 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolk and cream in small bowl.
Blend in about 1 cup of the hot soup.
Stir mixture in saucepan.
Ladle soup into 4 individual flame-proof bowls.
Float a slice of French bread on each and top with Parmesan cheese.
Broil, watching carefully, 4 inches from heat until cheese turns golden.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Grate cheese and mix with flour.
Stir in bacon, onion and green pepper. Spread in bottom of pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake on top of a cookie sheet for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned and filling is set.
Serves 6.
This can be made ahead of time.
Freezes well, cooked or uncooked.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix butter with stuffing.
Place half in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix zucchini with soup, sour cream, carrots and onion.
Pour into pan and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter; add seasonings.
Toss over cereal mix.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir often.
Enjoy!

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken. Wash chicken wings and disjoint.
Throw away tips.
Spray broiler pan heavily with Pam.
Place wings in a single layer in the pan.
Pour sauce over them. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently. Good for potluck.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line pizza pan with sugar cookie dough.
Spread cheese over dough.
Sprinkle sugar over cream cheese.
Arrange fruit on top as desired.

title: onion and potato gratin
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions with salt and pepper to taste in 3 tablespoons butter over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until they are golden. Spoon half the onions into a buttered 2-quart gratin dish, cover them with the potato slices and sprinkle the potatoes with salt and pepper. Cover the potatoes with the remaining onions.
Pour the cream over the mixture and sprinkle the mixture with Parmesan and Gruyere.
Dot the top with 3 tablespoons butter and bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: senator richard b. russell potatoes
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Pour into baking dish.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tomato and cheese.
Chill overnight.
Next day add tomato and cheese.
Mix well again.
Keep cold until time to serve.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°, uncover and bake until brown.

title: oven wedge fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Then cut each quarter into wedges (1/4 to 1/3-inch wide).
Coat cookie sheet with oil.
Lay wedges on cookie sheet, one side down.
Bake in oven about 7 minutes or until they start to brown, then flip potatoes over and sprinkle seasoning over top.
Bake 7 more minutes or until brown and potatoes are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry heaven cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, juice, vanilla and oil together; add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Batter is very stiff.
In a greased 9 x 11-inch pan, spread half the batter.
Spread about 1 1/2 cans of cherries.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Spread remaining batter on top.
Do your best to cover all the cherries. Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour and 325° last 1/2 hour.
My family's favorite!

title: june's cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in water and lime mixture for 12 hours in the refrigerator.
(Be sure water covers cucumbers.)
Remove cucumbers from lime water and rinse well.
Soak cucumbers in ice water for 12 hours in refrigerator.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and spices in large boiler, bring to boil and add cucumbers.
Boil 35 to 45 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: pork n' bean with ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in bacon drippings and melted butter.
Pour in beans, brown sugar, bell pepper and pimento. Pour in a little ketchup, mustard and barbecue sauce.
Let cook about 45 minutes in oven.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar. Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat in eggs until fluffy.
Put 1 whole vanilla wafer into paper cupcake liner and fill 1/2 to 3/4 full with cheese mixture. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Place a dollop of pie filling on top.
Makes 14 to 16.

title: crab devils
directions: Clean and mix crab meat.
Add egg, mustard, mayonnaise and seafood seasoning to taste.
Boil eggs.
Peel shells and cut in half lengthwise.
Take yellow out and mash.
Mix in 1/2 teaspoon mustard, 1/2 teaspoon mayonnaise, red pepper, salt and black pepper.
Stuff crab meat at bottom of egg.
Top with egg mixture. Sprinkle paprika on top and garnish with green pepper.

title: spicy sugared nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients in an 8-inch skillet over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted and nuts are coated, about 20 minutes.
Remove nuts from pan and cool on waxed paper. Break apart.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 3 cups.

title: jell-o salad
directions: Stir softened cream cheese and Jell-O into hot water.
Add pineapples and oranges.
Add marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 13 x 9 glass pan.
Cover top with pecans and oranges. Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir into pumpkin.
Add sugar, salt and spices. Stir in milk gradually.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer or until center is set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: italian lasagna
directions: Combine in a skillet and cook until brown the ground beef and olive oil.
Drain off all grease.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, oregano, basil, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and pepper. Simmer 1 hour.
Cook lasagna strips by package directions and drain.
Combine eggs and cottage cheese in a small bowl and mix well.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Put lasagna together in layers.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Stir well and bring to boil over medium heat.
Stir in condensed milk. Simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Stir in vanilla.

title: martha pafford's crackling cornbread
directions: Chop cracklings.
Barely cover the cracklings with hot water; let stand for 10 minutes.
Add cornmeal and egg.
Continue adding hot to warm water to mixture, enough to make dough into thick loaves.
Add salt to mixture.
Put in greased iron skillet.
Bake in oven at 400° to 450° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: hawaiian tea cookies
directions: Shape dough into two 2-inch diameter rolls.
Roll in colored sugar to coat.
Wrap tightly and chill 4 hours. Cut thin slices using sawing motion, 1/4-inch thick.
Place 1-inch apart on a greased sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy corn chowder
directions: Cook chicken; drain and save broths.
Saute celery and onion in large skillet coated with nonstick spray.
Add 3 cups chicken broth, water and milk.
Bring to boil.
Add corn and potato flakes. Stir in cheese.
Cook on low for 5 minutes and serve.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze 3 to 4 lemons, removing seeds.
Slice remaining lemons. Put in a 1-gallon container.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar.
Let stand at least 30 minutes.
This gives the sugar a chance to dissolve and the sugar will pull the juice from the lemon slices.
Add rest of sugar, water and ice.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Beat eggs; add margarine, sugar, banana and milk.
Cream together and add sifted dry ingredients.
Then add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 40 minutes or until done.
Knife inserted in center should come out clean.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill overnight.
Hollow out center of round loaf of bread.
Spoon dip in hollow and spread on chunks of bread.

title: oozy chocolate cupcakes(yield: 4 servings. can easily be doubled and prepared ahead.)
directions: 1. Butter and flour four 4-oz. ramekins, tap out excess flour.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: seafood surprise dip
directions: Mix all together well.
Add more Season-All to taste.
Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Serve with fresh veggies or crackers.

title: meed cake
directions: Spread out evenly in bottom of 13x11x1 pan. Bake at 350° until light brown---cool. Beat together and spread on crust: 8 oz. cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar and blend.
Then spread on cream cheese: 1pkg. instant vanilla pudding mixed and blended with 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Then spread on vanilla pudding:1 pkg. chocolate pudding mixed and blended with 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Top with layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into patties.
Brown quickly on both sides.
Cover with barbecue sauce and bake in oven at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, using a wire whisk or fork, beat the egg and egg whites until foamy.
Add milk, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat well; set aside.

Preheat the oven to 200 degrees. Lightly spray a large non-stick skillet with vegetable cooking spray; heat over medium heat. Dip 4 slices of bread into the egg mixture, turning to coat and draining excess back into dish. Place bread slices in prepared skillet. Cook until golden brown, turning once, about 1 to 2 minutes per side.
Transfer cooked slices to a plate; keep warm in oven.
Dip remaining slices in egg mixture, cook as directed. Spray skillet with vegetable cooking spray as needed.
Divide French toast amoung serving plates. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and top with maple syrup.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt together chocolate bits and oleo.
Cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows and mix.
Line aluminum foil box with foil.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Pour batter over top of this and firm log gently. Sprinkle coconut over all.
Fold over aluminum foil and press gently.
Refrigerate.
Cut in small slices to serve.

title: cheese ball(only 3 ingredients)
directions: Blend well and roll in chopped nuts.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add hamburger and cook until almost done.
Drain.
Add green pepper and cook until tender. Add taco sauce.

title: swiss cheese bread(quick, easy, delicious)
directions: Trim top and side crusts from bread, leaving bottom crust intact.
Make diagonal cuts, 1 inch thick, through the bread, but not through the bottom.

title: apple coconut salad
directions: Combine apple, celery and coconut.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix oil, orange juice, salt and paprika in a separate container. Fold in apple mixture.
Dot with plum jelly after arranged on bed of lettuce.
Serves 3.

title: crab balls
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in margarine.
In mixing bowl, blend herb seasoning, crabmeat, egg, catsup, mayonnaise and pepper.
Add green pepper, onion and celery.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Place balls on cookie sheet.
