Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in fridge (preferably overnight).

title: shrimp and crabmeat loaf
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Hollow out each to about 1/4-inch.
Mix all the ingredients and stuff into the bread.
Wrap in foil and chill until firm.
Slice.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare Bundt pan by coating the inside with cooking spray or butter and set aside.

title: julianne's fudge
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cocoa together in a ziploc bag.
Pour in bowl.
Lay stick of butter on top of mixture.
Add cream to mix over butter.
Do not stir.
Microwave on high for 2 minutes. Remove and stir well until thick.
Butter dish; pour into dish and let stand or refrigerate until firm.

title: lime broiled catfish
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in lime juice, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well. Remove from heat and set aside.
Place fillets in a shallow baking dish.
Brush each fillet generously with lime-butter sauce.
Broil for 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Remove to a warm serving dish. Spoon pan juices over each fillet.
Garnish with lime and parsley, if desired.
(I usually do the whole recipe in a skillet so I don't have to clean the oven!)
Serves 2.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy, add vanilla, oil and zucchini.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to liquid ingredients.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for one hour at 325°.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Combine flour, butter and brown sugar and press into 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and break up; leave in pan.

title: german short ribs
directions: Coat short ribs in mixture of 2 tablespoons of flour with salt and pepper.
Melt shortening in large skillet or slow cooking pot with browning unit; add ribs and brown on all sides.
Pour off excess fat.
In slow-cooking pot, combine ribs, onions, wine, chili sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and chili powder.
Cover and cook on low for six to eight hours.
Turn control to high.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons of flour that has been dissolved in a small amount of the meat juices.
Cook on high for 10 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese and milk, blending until completely smooth.
Stir in chipped beef, onion, green pepper, garlic pepper and ginger.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour beef mixture into a glass pie plate or shallow baking dish.
In a small skillet, saute nuts in butter until thoroughly glazed.
Sprinkle nuts over beef mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serve hot with crackers.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Sugar or sweeten to taste.
Wait 24 hours to eat.
Will last up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: cherry cobbler bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Mix flour and baking powder.
In large bowl, beat butter and confectioners sugar with mixer until fluffy.
Beat in egg and lemon peel.
With mixer on low speed, gradually add flour mixture.
Remove 2/3 dough.
With floured fingers, pat remaining dough over bottom of pan.
Spread pie filling over dough to edges of pan.
Roll reserved dough into 1-inch balls.
Flatten slightly and place evenly on pie filling. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool in pan. Dust with powdered sugar before cutting.
Makes 18.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs, flour, milk and baking powder with rotary beater until smooth.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Then add flour, vanilla and pecans. Roll by hand into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot. Cool, then roll again in confectioners sugar.

title: summer lasagna
directions: Cook the noodles according to package directions. Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Saute in a large skillet or Dutch oven. Saute chopped onion and mushroom slices (small can if halving recipe).
Add chicken. Stir. Add spaghetti sauce, Italian seasoning, oregano and garlic. Stir.
Heat through, 10 minutes. Grate Mozzarella cheese. Combine 2 egg whites, parsley flakes (to taste) and a large container of cottage cheese.
Spread small amount of sauce on bottom of Pyrex dish (sprayed with Pam, Mazola, etc.).
Layer noodles, cottage cheese mix, Romano cheese, sauce, Mozzarella cheese, etc.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Let set 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Makes two 9 x 13-inch dishes.

title: easy quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs together; add 1/2 of container of half and half.
Mix in cooked meat and vegetable (couple slices each).
Use your own judgment how much.
Mix in 1 to 2 cups of cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
You may have enough for 2. Sprinkle with pepper.
Cook until quiche is firm, about 30 to 45 minutes. (You can check with a fork.
It will be fluffy and not too runny.)

title: margaret's cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil in large saucepan. Add salt. Stir in grits slowly. Reduce heat to low. Cover. Cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, margarine and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir 1/4 of the mixture into the eggs, then combine with remaining grits.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until set and lightly browned.
Knife should come out clean.

title: jam cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: elly's polish cole slaw
directions: Set aside first 5 ingredients.
Place remaining ingredients in saucepan on stove.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover and let stand on countertop for 3 hours, then refrigerate.
Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Bone chicken.
Place in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan. Place the package of Doritos on top of the chicken.
In a mixing bowl, combine mushroom and chicken soups, broth and Ro-Tel.
Mix until lumps are gone.
Pour this mixture over the Doritos and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broiled shrimp
directions: Slit unshelled shrimp down back, cutting 3/4 way through to remove sand veins.
Marinate shrimp for 2 hours in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Place shrimp in a broiling pan and pour marinade over shrimp.
Broil 7 or 8 minutes, turning once.
Use as appetizer.
Serves 4.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place eggs, sugar and vinegar in double boiler.
Cook, beating constantly until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
When cooled, fold in whipped cream, fruit and marshmallows.
Pour in mold and chill 24 hours.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together (tuna, noodles, soup and olives). Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat the eggs with mixer at high speed for 5 minutes. Gradually add the granulated sugar. Stir in the pumpkin filling, lemon juice, plain flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Spread in greased (spray Pam) 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Top with nuts. Bake at 370° for 15 to 20 minutes. Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll at narrow end, cloth and cake together.
Let cool.
Unroll and spread filling on cake and re-roll.

title: lemon cheese icing
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add half and half, butter, sugar, lemon juice, lemon peel, vanilla and salt.
Beat until fluffy.
Tint pale yellow with food coloring, blending well. Add more sugar or cream, if necessary, for good spreading consistency.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together well the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and yeast.
Mix in shortening.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
If needed, add more flour to make soft dough.
Shape as desired.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
The dough may be stored in the refrigerator before baking.
Dough does not have to rise before baking.

title: angel food cake
directions: Put egg whites in bowl.
Throw salt over them.
Beat until foamy.
Sift in the cream of tartar.
Beat this until it will stand alone in bowl.
Sift in the sugar, a tablespoon at a time. Stir.
Sift in the flour.
Stir vanilla just enough to mix.
Angel food pan should be rinsed with cold water.
Put in cake pan.
Set oven at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour or a little longer if it needs browning more.
Invert pan on wire rack for 1 hour before removing cake from pan.

title: miniature biscuits supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk all at once and stir until dough follows fork around bowl. Place dough on lightly floured surface, gently patting out dough to 3/4-inch thick. Use either small biscuit cutter or a knife which works quite well in getting the desired size and a unique shape. They can be cut into miniature diamonds or any shape desired. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet. Yield: 8 to 10 tiny biscuits.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg, honey and extract and mix well.
Combine flour and baking soda and beat into butter-sugar mixture.
Batter will be very stiff.
Using your hands, roll small pieces of dough into size of a large marble. Place on buttered baking sheets.
Flatten with bottom of a heavy glass.
May have to dip glass in flour.
Place almond on each cookie and paint each cookie with egg-water.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour batter into well greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth. Pour evenly over cake batter. Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt tube pan; sprinkle nuts into bottom of the pan.
Place cake mix and pudding mix in a bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon rum, oil, eggs and 1 cup water; mix for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan; bake at 325° for 50 minutes, or until done.
Remove from oven.

title: red red punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the last three; bring to a boil.
Pour into a bowl.
Float orange slices and lemon slices, topped with half a cherry.
Red food coloring may be added, if desired.
Yield: 20 punch cup servings.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 1- 1 1/2 hrs. at 350°.

title: cone cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ice cream cones with flat bottoms (fill cones completely).
Set in a loaf pan and cook at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until they spring back when touched on top.
Top with your favorite icing.

title: fresh spinach casserole
directions: Wash, cook and drain spinach.
Combine spinach, soup, egg, nutmeg and cheese.
Put in a 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs in melted butter; add garlic and red pepper.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french tomato soup(soup a la tomate)
directions: You will need a blender or electric mixer.

title: paris puffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 muffin cups (mini muffin pans work great too).

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in water.
Add Bix-Mix and beat.
Add mustard and 1 cup cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn batter into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack before slicing.
The slices are great toasted and served with chili or a green salad.
Also makes great croutons.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 3 (20 ounce) cans.
Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk.
Blend in dry ingredients and stir in.
Add nuts and bananas.
Pour into pan and bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Combine the coconut, peanut butter, cracker crumbs, vanilla, oleo, sugar and nuts.
Melt the wax and chocolate together; roll the first mixture into small balls and dip in chocolate mixture. Place on waxed paper to dry.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix together cream cheese and marshmallow cream until well blended.
Gradually beat in brown sugar and continue beating on low speed for 5 minutes, until well blended and brown sugar is well dissolved.
Excellent for dipping strawberries or your favorite fruit.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix the mashed potatoes into the hot water on the mixer, using a flat beater.
Add the salt, cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add the grated cheese and the green onions.
Blend in. Pour into a buttered deep pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hot through.

title: plain cheese pizza
directions: Mix with mixer for 5 minutes.
Then add another 1/4 cup flour and 1/4 cup water.
Mix again for 2 minutes.
Put dough on a pizza pan.
Take rolling pin and roll north, south, east and west.
Then roll northwest, northeast, southeast and southwest.
Then take tomato sauce and spread on dough.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on tomato sauce.
Put in oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Take out and enjoy.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in other ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix soda and dates.
Pour hot water over them; let cool.
Add margarine; let melt.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: mother's baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients, except chicken, and pour in large mixing bowl.
Cut chicken breasts and put into mixture; let stand overnight.
Toast bread and roll fine into bread crumbs.
Melt butter and shortening together.
Take chicken out of mixture (you may want to wipe some off).
Roll in bread crumbs and put in baking dish.
Pour half of melted butter and shortening over it. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Pour rest of butter mixture over chicken and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: homemade ice cream(strawberry)
directions: In a clean 13-ounce coffee can, mix together the milk, cream, juice and vanilla. Put on the lid and place the can in a clean 34-ounce coffee can.
Fill the remaining space in the large can with ice and cover the ice with salt.
Put on the lid and place the can on the floor.
Roll the can back and forth for 10 minutes. Open up both cans.
Scrape down the sides of the smaller can and stir in 1 cup strawberries.
Replace the small lid.
Pour out the excess water out of the larger can and add more ice and salt.
Put larger lid back on and roll the cans for 5 to 7 more minutes. Makes 8 small servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together apples, sugar and nuts and let stand 1 hour or overnight.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to apple mixture.
Add cooking oil, eggs and vanilla and blend well. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Make toothpick test to see if done.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: quick jello salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple.
Add pineapple to dry Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese; stir.
Add whipped cream, stir and refrigerate.

title: valentine sugar cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and extracts.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Chill several hours.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2 or 3-inch heart shaped cookie cutter.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet; sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: 50 minute strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients together with electric mixer.
Dissolve jello and water together.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Do not open oven door before the 50 minutes are up.
This is a very temperamental cake.
Do not substitute any ingredients.
It will not turn out right if you do.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine pineapple, jello and sugar.
Let come to a boil, then let cool.
Then add cream cheese, apricot baby food and Cool Whip, mixing well together.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: cream gravy
directions: In pan drippings, over medium heat, add flour and stir until browned.
Gradually add hot milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve hot over mashed potatoes or biscuits.

title: louisa adams' crab lasagne
directions: Mix
together all wet ingredients except grated cheese. Do not cook noodles.
They'll cook in the casserole.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch casserole: 1/2 the noodles, 1/2 crab mixture and 1/2 grated cheese.
Repeat.
Cook
1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
This freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: date rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a mixing bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla. Stir in rice and dates. Pour into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, stirring 20 minutes, or until set.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the melted butter with the sugar. Add the peanut butter and Rice Krispies. Mixture will be soft. Refrigerate until cooled. When cooled, form into small balls. Dip in the melted chocolate chips and paraffin wax. Place on wax paper.

title: zucchini moussaka(zucchini, beef and cheese casserole)
directions: In skillet, brown zucchini and onion lightly in oil; remove from skillet and place in bottom of shallow 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
In same skillet, brown beef; pour off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic, salt and cinnamon; spoon over zucchini and onion.
Blend egg and cottage cheese; spoon over meat.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients adding eggs one at a time, beating about one minute after each.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 layers or bake in 9x13 inch pan.

title: crunchy cucumber pickles
directions: Slice pickles, onions and peppers and mix.
Add 1 tablespoon salt and mix.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Stir after 2 hours and drain off any liquid.
Add vinegar, sugar and the celery seed.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand for 4 hours, mixing about every hour.
Place in jar and refrigerate.
Use as desired. Recipe will feed 8.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Simmer large chicken until tender.
Let cool in broth.
Remove meat from bones in small chunks.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place sugar in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until it's liquified and golden brown.
Add water; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add syrup and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Layer bread, raisins and half the cheese in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Pour syrup mixture over bread and top with rest of cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Brown onions in butter for about 4 minutes.
Add broccoli and simmer for
8 to 10 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup, cup of cooked rice
and
small
jar
Cheez Whiz.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook the rice; combine with all of the ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 35 or 45 minutes, stirring twice.

title: ranchero macaroni bake
directions: In large bowl, combine soup and milk.
Stir in cooked macaroni, cheese and salsa.
Spoon into 3-quart dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Stir, sprinkle chips over macaroni mixture. Bake 5 minutes or until bubbling.

title: old timey milk toast
directions: Mix butter (or cream) and sugar into good spreading texture, ready to spread on biscuit halves and toast to lightly browned. Place toasted biscuits in cereal dishes and pour scalded milk over the toast.
Use your own judgement on amount of butter (or cream), sugar and flavoring to add to milk.

title: veal cutlets ala marsala-lemon
directions: This is a delicate dish.
Bread cutlets with flour, then salt and pepper them.
Brown in hot oil individually and remove.
Place cutlets back in pan (do not crowd).
Pour on Marsala wine and simmer for 2 minutes. Add 1/2 cup chicken broth, sprinkle with chopped parsley and squeeze whole lemon on top. Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer about 2 or 3 minutes.
Keep warm in pan with cover.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and salt until lemon colored.
Add the butter and flour and blend well.
Add milk; fold in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into shell and top with the rest of the coconut.
Bake at 325° for about 60 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion in Pam-sprayed baking dish; season each layer with salt and pepper. Mix mushroom soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake in 350° oven 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: wheat bread
directions: Mix well and pour into	greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.	Great with kettle of soup.

title: bread pudding #2
directions: Place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish the bread crumbs.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Place in baking dish in pan of hot water 1 inch deep.
Bake until knife comes out clean.
Serve warm with lemon sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grandma kinney's spaghetti casserole
directions: Add most of one jar of Prego to ground beef.
Cream together sour cream and cream cheese.
Pour a little sauce to the bottom of a lasagne pan.
Cover with 1/2 spaghetti; spread on 1/2 creamed mixture.
Sprinkle on 1/2 cheese.
Cover with 1/2 sauce. Repeat layers, adding sauce last.
Sprinkle on remaining Mozzarella.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy company salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir in Ranch dressing right before serving.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Stir together pie filling, cherries and 2 tablespoons flour. Stir in almond extract. Place in lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Trim crusts from bread slices and cut slices into strips. Arrange
bread strips over fruit mixture in pattern of choice. Stir together remaining 2 tablespoons of flour, sugar, butter, egg and lemon rind. Drizzle over bread strips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk together and boil 1 minute.
Remove from fire; add chocolate chips.
Beat until thick.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add salt and minced onion.
Boil until tender.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Place chicken in large casserole dish.
Pour chicken broth over the chicken.
Spread soup over top.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix well, then roll into round balls.
The candy probably could be formed into a long roll and sliced.

title: danish red mush
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add tapioca, cinnamon and sugar.
Cook about 6 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly, until tapioca is clear. Remove from heat.
Add cherries and juice; mix well.
Serve hot or cold.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
May serve with cream.

title: lela's oatmeal pie
directions: Mix altogether and pour in unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Prepare pie mix according to package directions.
Melt oleo; pour in 11 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place dough in bottom of pan and flatten.
Bake for 15 or 20 minutes or until done.
Pour rest of ingredients (peaches, juice and 1 cup of sugar on top of dough).
Make second crust and place on top of ingredients.
Make slits in dough and pour 1/2 cup of sugar on top.
Bake at 375° approximately 35 to 45 minutes or until done (brown).

title: jiffy corn fritters(sweet)
directions: Heat milk until scalding hot.
Add to Jiffy mix and mix well. Mixture should be stiff.
Allow to cool, then stir in 1 small egg. In a small amount of cooking oil, fry on both sides until golden brown.

title: florida fruit pie
directions: Drain cherries, mix with pineapple and cook over low heat until mixed.
Add flour, sugar, coloring and cook until thick. While still warm, add jello and bananas.
Cool and add nuts. Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
Cover pie with whipped cream before serving.
Wonderful.

title: skillet chilli beans
directions: Brown meat with onions and green pepper in a large skillet. Add beans with liquid to meat after all redness is gone.
Pour in tomato sauce, salt and chili powder.
Stir and simmer on low heat. Occasionally, stir until chili is desired thickness, about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: tuna melts
directions: Mix tuna, cheese, onion and Miracle Whip together.
Spoon into buns. Wrap in foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions into a 1 gallon jar.
Add salt, then cover with water for 3 hours minimum.
Drain and rinse. For the juice, mix remaining ingredients.
Bring this to a boil, then add pickles and cook for 10 minutes.
Put in clean, hot jars and seal.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In skillet, melt butter and brown chicken over medium heat for 4 minutes, turning once.
Stir in golden herb with lemon recipe soup mix, blended with water. Arrange lemon slices on chicken.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 10 minutes, or until sauce is slightly thickened and chicken is done.
Serve chicken over rice, then spoon sauce over chicken.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet at medium heat.
Add rice and stir constantly until rice is golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add consomme, mushrooms, onion, salt and pepper; mix well.
Bake, covered, in greased 2-quart (1892-ml) casserole at 350° (177°C) for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together, beating in the eggs one at a time. Pour into crust.
Bake 50 minutes at 375° or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: to can apple pie filling
directions: Peel and cut up the apples.
Pack into quart jars.

title: apricot oatmeal bars
directions: Combine apricots and water in covered pan. Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes. Remove cover and cook until water has all evaporated. Add preserves, sugar and vanilla.
Stir until preserves melt.
Cool to room temperature.

title: fudge
directions: Put the sugar, milk, salt and vanilla over low heat and let come a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add marshmallows. Stir until melted. Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
When chips are melted, pour quickly into buttered dish.
Cut or tear marshmallows into small pieces.

title: noodles italiano
directions: In skillet, brown beef with onion, garlic and salt.
Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole with soup, water and noodles.
Place cheese around the edges.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Into flour, baking powder and salt, stir in milk and oil. Blend in nuts, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1 cup brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour over entire batter 2 cups hot water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: last minute supper
directions: Lightly brown meat and onion in oleo; drain.
Blend in soup and milk.
Add potatoes and seasoning; place in a 375° to 400° oven until heated through.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Stir together the remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill overnight.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn soup
directions: Combine 1/3 to 1/2 of corn and all of stock in blender; puree. In a 3-quart saucepan combine corn mixture with remaining whole corn and butter; simmer slowly for 5 minutes, stirring.
Add milk, garlic, oregano, chicken, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and add chilis.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Dip into bowls; top with cheese and serve.
Serves 6.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place all ingredients in a medium size saucepan; stir and cover tightly.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes, or until carrots are tender and glazed and most of liquid has cooked away. Stir to coat.

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and spices.
Work in shortening as in making baking powder biscuits.
Set aside 1 cupful.
Mix together beaten egg and milk, then add soda and baking powder. Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cream butter. Add sugar gradually. Add eggs one at a time, beat well after each addition. Add salt and chocolate. Blend and add sifted flour and vanilla.

title: potato pizza
directions: Brown hamburger. Add onion, salt, and pepper, set aside. Mix potatoes, cheese soup, and milk in a baking dish. Top with hamburger mixture. Mix tomato sauce and oregano and put on top of hamburger mixture. Bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and top with cheeses and return to oven to melt cheeses.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in well-greased dish.

title: connie's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a baking pan on top of stove on medium heat.
Add brown sugar to melted butter and stir until evenly mixed.
Arrange pineapple or other fruit and nuts onto sugar mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add shortening to dry ingredients in a bowl.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic; add clams and juice.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cheese; cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve over linguini, cooked al dente.

title: aunt gail's broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli pieces and place in a medium size bowl.
Add onion, cheese and bacon; mix well.
In a small bowl combine Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well and put over salad ingredients.
Place a few croutons on top if desired.

title: irish cream
directions: In blender container, blend all ingredients at low speed until foamy.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate up to 4 weeks. Blend or shake well before serving.
Makes 18 (1/3 cup) servings.

title: creamy pineapple cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Meanwhile, simmer crushed pineapple and powdered sugar.
Remove cake from oven.
Poke holes in it.
Cover with pineapple and chill.
Mix instant pudding as directed on the box and add coconut.
Spread over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.
Delicious!

title: microwave tapioca
directions: Combine sugar, tapioca, milk and egg in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
(This is very important.)
Cook on High until mixture comes to a full boil, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in lemon juice and rind; beat in egg yolks, then melted butter.
Stir in milk.
Beat egg whites with salt until fairly stiff peaks form, then fold into lemon mixture until no streaks of white show.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes or until crust is lightly browned and filling puffy and touched with brown.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting.
Good warm or cold.

title: carrot marshmallow salad
directions: Peel carrots and shred with a coarse shredder into mixing bowl.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, raisins and coconut.
Toss lightly to mix.
Combine mayo with carrot mixture.
Carefully fold in whipped cream.
Serve in crisp lettuce cups.
Garnish top with additional coconut, if desired.

title: no cholesterol fudge cake
directions: Spray a 9-inch spring-form pan with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except chocolate chips and raisins.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes. Batter will be very thin.
Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and raisins over top.
Bake at 325° until top of cake is firm to touch, 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool at least 30 minutes.
Loosen edges of cake with knife before removing from pan.
Cover to keep moist.

title: meal in a muffin
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl by hand until well blended.
Spoon into muffin pans, filling 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until tests done.
Can use paper liners or grease pans.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients and stir well.
Stir in pecans. Pour mixture into a pastry shell.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Serve with ice cream.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Freeze to firm.
Yields 1 serving.

title: crawfish jambalaya in rice cooker
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into rice cooker. Turn on rice cooker and set. After the bell rings, allow jambalaya to stay on warm cycle for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: apple butter(mom's recipe)
directions: Wash apples; do not peel.
Cut in fourths and remove seeds. Cook until tender with a small amount of water.
Run through Foley mill.
Return to kettle.
Sweeten to taste.
Add cinnamon and cloves to taste.
Cook slowly over low heat, stirring quite often to keep from sticking, until it is cooked to right consistency and color.
Fill clean, sterilized jars and seal.
May also freeze, if desired.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes.
Melt butter.
Cook onions in butter until tender.
Add potatoes and cook 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Salt and pepper.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water.
Add pineapple and oranges. Mix and place in refrigerator until cools and just starts to thicken.
Blend in the sour cream and top with toasted pecans. Return to refrigerator and allow to congeal.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Cover sheet with graham crackers, solid and tight.
Boil margarine and sugar 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake for 8 minutes; remove and sprinkle with chocolate chips while hot.
Spread chocolate.
Put into freezer for 15 minutes.
Remove and break into pieces.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except dressing and butter, and place in buttered casserole.
Top with Pepperidge Farm herb dressing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar until it looks like dough. Roll out with rolling pin. Spread with peanut butter and roll up as a jelly roll. Cool and slice.

title: cherry cheese cupcakes
directions: Beat until smooth and creamy.
Line two (12-hole) cupcake pans with foil liners.
Place one wafer in each.
Fill 3/4 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with filling.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in water until soft; drain.
Crumble bread.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375°; check in 15 minutes.
Cook just until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: If cake is large, double recipe. Bring to a boil in saucepan for 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Beat mixture until cool and until desired consistency is reached.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Combine rice, corn, chopped onion, green pepper and hamburg.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in pineapple. Sift flour, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Gradually stir into first mixture.
Mix in nuts.
Chill for 1 hour.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion.
Add oil in slow stream, beating constantly with electric or rotary beater.
May also use blender.
Yields 2 cups.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of sugar in an iron skillet slowly until brown and runny.
Mix egg, oleo and remaining sugar with milk in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat until oleo melts.
Turn heat to medium and add browned sugar.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°). Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla.
Beat until spreading consistency.
If icing gets too thick, add a little milk.
This covers a 2-layer cake.

title: deep dish pizza chicago style
directions: Heat sausages and 1/4 cup water to boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Continue to cook, turning sausage frequently until well browned (about 20 minutes).
Drain sausage on paper towel.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix hot roll mix (and yeast) from package with oil and 1 1/2 cups hot water to form soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface, 5 minutes.
Pat dough onto bottom and halfway up sides of pan to make a stand-up edge.
Cover.
Let rise at room temperature, 15 minutes.

title: summer italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Refrigerate several more hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili sauce
directions: Drain off juice from cooked tomatoes.
Mix vegetables, salt and sugar.
Cook slowly about 3 1/2 hours.
Add vinegar and spices; can.
Makes 5 pints.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook buttermilk, sugar, brown sugar, oleo and baking soda over medium-low heat until mixture forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.

title: honey almond sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and peel. Cut in half lengthwise. Place in a single layer in a greased baking pan. Combine honey,

marmalade, water and salt. Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes. Pour over potatoes. Melt margarine in a small frying pan, add almonds and toast over low heat until golden. Sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until glazed, basting occasionally.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne by directions on box.
Brown ground beef; drain. Add Prego sauce and mushrooms to ground beef.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Put a layer of lasagne in pan.
Add 1/2 beef mixture. Add another layer of lasagne, then other half beef mixture plus Ricotta cheese.
Finish with rest of lasagne and add shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable rice mix
directions: In a 2 quart casserole, combine the carrot, green pepper, onions and butter; cover.
Microwave on High for 4 to 8 minutes or until the vegetables are tender, stirring once during cooking time. Makes 4 servings.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Pour hot water over jello; when dissolved, add gelatin which has been softened.
Add orange juice; sit in refrigerator to congeal slightly.
Grind cranberries and orange, cut in quarters (leave peel on).
Mix with chopped celery and chopped pecans.
Pour 2 cups of sugar over ground ingredients and let stand for 30 minutes, then mix in jello and pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
This will fill a green Tupperware circular mold with the hole in the center.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Do not add salt.
Add package of taco mix with amount of water called for on package.
Add mushroom soup with about 1/4 cup water or just rinse can.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Chop cookies in blender or in a plastic bag with a rolling pin.
Reserve 3/4 cup chopped cookies for garnish. Melt butter and mix with remaining cookie crumbs.

Pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread softened ice cream over cookies, drizzle fudge topping over the ice cream and spread Cool Whip over the fudge topping. Sprinkle the reserved cookie crumbs over the Cool Whip.
Freeze for at least one hour.
Remove from freezer and thaw for a few minutes before serving.

title: fried fish batter
directions: Mix ingredients together. Dredge fish in cornmeal mixture and fry at 350° until golden brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften and cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit (apples, grapes, melons, strawberries, kiwi, etc.)

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend the two cheeses together in a double boiler.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cheese mixture.
Dip bread cubes into cheese mixture and arrange cubes on baking sheet.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, brown cubes in a 375° oven and serve warm with salads or light summer meals. Good!

title: crab or crawfish casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into rice cooker.
Cook until done.
Do not cook ahead.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 8 Milky Ways and 1 stick butter.
Set aside.
Cream together
stick
butter
and 2 cups sugar.
Then add 4 eggs. Sift
flour and soda and add to creamed mixture with 1 1/4 cups buttermilk.
Then
add
Milky
Way
mixture.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake for 1 hour 10 minutes at 325° or until done in 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.

title: meatball soup
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients together. Form in small quarter size balls.
Brown in skillet with oil.
In a large pot, combine the remaining ingredients.
Add the browned meat.
Boil for 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Spread refried beans on platter or in bowl.
Spread sour cream over beans.
Spread picante sauce over sour cream and swirl through the cream slightly, but not down into beans.
Sprinkle cheese over sour cream.
Top with chopped onions, olives and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips or any chips you desire. Very good!

title: sweet freezer pickles
directions: Put 1 tablespoon salt over all of the ingredients.
Let stand 2 hours.
Pour off liquid.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup vinegar and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Will keep in refrigerator three weeks or freeze.

title: layered salad for group
directions: Layer first six ingredients in order given in 9 x 13 pan or glass dish.
Mix Miracle Whip with sugar and spread on top of lettuce mixture.
Scatter peas, then cheese on top of mixture in pan (do not mix).
Refrigerate 24 hours to set.
Very good!

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt in a small mixing bowl until thick and creamy.
Set aside.

title: shredded potato and ham pie
directions: In a bowl combine eggs, vegetables, ham, 1/2 cup cheese, milk and onions; set aside.
Combine potatoes and 1/2 cup cheese.
Press in bottom and sides of ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Pour filling into potato-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sixty minute batter rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Beat well with spoon.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Put in greased muffin pan.
Let rise for 15 minutes. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan roll
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Pour about half of mixture onto waxed paper.
The mixture will seem dry.
Moisten hands with water and squeeze mixture into roll.
Make second roll. Wrap in waxed paper; chill and slice.

title: elizabeth pond's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions, then brown meat in olive oil.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Place wax and chocolate chips into top of a double boiler. Heat until both are melted.
Stir well.
Using a toothpick to pick up balls, dip each ball into chocolate.

title: party mix
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
In a small
microwave measuring cup (or dish) heat the oil until hot (1 minute on High).
Add the cinnamon and curry powder.
Mix well. Coat cereal well. Cook 2 minutes on High in microwave. Stir well. Cook another 2 minutes on High.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: doughnuts
directions: Scald milk; add shortening to milk and stir until dissolved. Add sugar. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water, then add to mixture. Add 1 cup of flour to mixture.
Add egg and remaining flour; knead and roll out, then cut.
Cook in hot shortening.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cover in refrigerator 7 to 8 hours to marinate.
Turn over once or twice.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 350° or in shallow pan for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: gravy mix
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Store in pint jar with tight fitting lid at room temperature.
Shake before using.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, vanilla, almond extract and goes in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar. Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Roll dough 1/2-inch to 1/4-inch thick and cut as desired.

title: ahi pasta
directions: Saute ahi in olive oil and onions for 2 to 3 minutes until fish is medium rare.
Add tomatoes, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add basil and oregano.
Stir and serve over cooked pasta.
Garnish with capers. Serves two.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Blend the whipped topping with the peanut butter mixture.
Pour into prepared crust; top with 8 ounces whipped topping.
Chill before serving.
This makes two pies.

title: senator's salad(serves 12)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in large bowl.
Bring to a boil the sugar, vegetable oil and vinegar.
Pour over the vegetables and toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: kielbasa
directions: Combine everything in crock-pot; cook on high for 1 hour then turn to low for 5 hours.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Cut
chicken breasts in cubes.	Cover bottom of skillet with soy
sauce	and
add
oleo.
Let mixture get hot.
Place chicken cubes in skillet and cook.	Before all of sauce cooks into meat, sprinkle sesame seed on top.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together, then add vanilla, egg and water.
Mix together.
In a separate bowl, combine flour and oats, then gradually add to mix.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix or fold gently.
Pour in buttered and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If you like, add 1 cup Mozzarella to the mixture.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets.
Cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender.
When beets are cold, slip skins.
To make 5 quarts beets into pickles, bring ingredients to a boil (except beets). Add beets, bring to a boil and put in cans to which a stick of cinnamon has been added.
Put beets into cans that are hot.
Put lids on and let cool.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Pat mixture on bottom of spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese; gradually beat in 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Divide batter in half.
Stir melted chocolate into first half.
Pour chocolate batter onto crust.
Cover with plain batter and marbleize.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Shut off oven and open door.
Leave cheesecake in oven for 30 additional minutes.
Cool at room temperature and refrigerate.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch slightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle small amount of Parmesan cheese on top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not get too brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage strata
directions: Fit bread into the bottom of a greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Stir in the mustard. Spoon sausage evenly over the bread.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs, milk and Worcestershire sauce and pour over cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 325° or until set.

title: baked greek chicken
directions: Wash chicken completely.
Mix all ingredients well.
Marinate chicken for 12 hours. After 6 hours, mix marinade and turn the breasts over.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in a metal pan (12 3/4 x 9 x 2 1/4-inches).
Pour remaining marinade in pan. Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and turn chicken over.
Continue for 20 minutes or until done.
Serve with rice and broccoli or other vegetable.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Quarter and drain artichoke hearts and place in bottom of dish. Thaw and drain spinach and arrange over artichokes.
Pepper.
Mix together the cream cheese, butter and milk.
Pour over spinach and artichokes. Sprinkle with Parmesan and bake for 40 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix salt and boiling water.
Add flour, baby oil and alum; mix well together.
Divide into 4 equal parts.
Add food coloring and knead.
Store in plastic bags inside plastic container.
Does not need to be refrigerated.

title: crouton soup
directions: Boil chicken with onion, celery, salt and pepper until well done.
Remove meat from bone.
Wash and cut up endive.
Add to chicken broth.
When it starts to boil, drop in tiny meatballs. Simmer 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Thaw bread in refrigerator overnight.
From each loaf, shape 12 (1/2-inch) balls.
Roll each ball into a rope about 14 inches long.
Shape into pretzels by forming a knot and looping ends through.
Arrange pretzels 1 inch apart on well-greased baking sheet.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Brush combined egg white and water on pretzels, then sprinkle with salt.
Place a shallow pan containing 1 inch of boiling water on lower rack in the oven. Bake pretzels on a cookie sheet on a rack above water at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Cook pudding; allow to cool slightly.
Drain fruit cocktail and add it to coconut and pudding; mix well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt together and stir into banana mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pineapple juice with electric mixer.
Mix well.
Add pineapple juice to achieve the thickness desired.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat and stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper and heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake 1 hour
in 350° oven.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in sheet cake pan.
When done, while hot, poke holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake. Then pour bottle of chocolate syrup over cake.
Cool.

title: irish stew
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add equal amounts tomato sauce and water. Add remaining ingredients.	Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Well worth the time involved!

title: sherri's scramble
directions: Mix thoroughly.
(Use large container.)
Bake in 2 large oven roasting pans at 250° for a total of 2 hours.
Stir at 15 minute intervals; use wooden spoon.

title: texas cake
directions: Combine butter, water and cocoa in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour and sugar. Mix well.
Add the egg, vanilla and sour cream and mix well.
Pour in greased 13 x 18-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Fifteen minutes before cake is done, prepare icing.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; stir in lemon juice and set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in a small mixing bowl; cream until light.
Add cooled gelatin mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Beat milk in a large chilled mixing bowl until firm peaks form.
Stir in cheese mixture.
Spoon filling into two 9-inch graham cracker crusts.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: viennese fingers
directions: Grease several cookie sheets and dust with flour.

title: texas torte no. 1
directions: Add flour, salt and milk to the beaten eggs and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into 8 x 12 dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl all ingredients on low speed until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° or until cake is golden brown or springs back when touched.

title: mama's glorious golden fruitcake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; reserve 1/4 cup. Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Combine walnuts, raisins, pineapple, candied cherries, lemon rind and 1/4 cup flour.
Stir into batter.
Spread batter in greased and waxed paper-lined 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 275° oven 2 hours and 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 30 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap fruitcake tightly in foil.
Store in refrigerator up to 4 weeks.
(Fruitcake keeps better if stored and unfrosted.)

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour rice slowly into boiling salt water in large pan.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook exactly 5 minutes.
Water will be absorbed. Add milk and butter, stir a little, bring to boil, cover and cook over over low until rice is soft, 20 to 30 minutes.
Beat eggs and sugar, add vanilla and raisins.
Pour egg mixture into rice slowly until it thickens.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well and save juice.
Place fruit in layers in a 2-quart ovenproof dish with nuts and cherries on top.
Bring syrup ingredients to a boil.
Pour over fruit and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Stir in rice, salts, soup and water.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Combine with other ingredients.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in buttered oblong baking pan.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients and beat hard.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 inch loaf pan at 350°F 45-50 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mother's meat loaf (bacon and dill)
directions: Prepare bread crumbs, minced onion and pickles.
In large bowl, beat eggs with fork.
Lightly mix in chopped beef, add bread crumbs, onion, mustard, milk and ketchup along with all ingredients.
Shape meat into a loaf and place in shallow baking dish.
Spread ketchup on top of loaf.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
When done, pour off excess juices.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Pour milk into a 4 cup measure.
Microwave on high 3 to 4 minutes or until steaming.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spray jelly roll or pizza pan or cookie sheet with pam. Spread crescent rolls onto pan.
Push seams together to make pizza crust.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned. Mix cream cheese, sour cream, and dip together.
Spread over cooled crust like pizza sauce.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Just put all ingredients in a crock-pot and let simmer on low heat.

title: cool summer pasta
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Cook vegetables.
Chop peppers into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients, but add desired amount of Italian dressing.
Allow to cool.
Serve with bread as a cool summer meal.
For best results, allow pasta to cool in refrigerator for eight hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put everything in blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Drain both cans of pineapple into a bowl.
Add the pudding; beat until thickened.
Add the mandarin oranges to the pineapple with the sliced bananas.
Add the Tang.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: piccadilly carrot souffle
directions: Stem or boil carrots until extra soft. Drain well. While carrots are warm, add sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Whip with mixer until smooth. Add flour and mix well. Whip eggs and add to flour mixture; blend well. Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish about half full as the souffle will rise. Bake in 350° oven for about an hour or until top is a light golden brown. Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar over the top before serving.

title: pasta el pollo
directions: Saute shallots and garlic in olive oil for 30 seconds; add wine and simmer until reduced by half.
Add cream and mustard. Simmer on medium heat until mixture thickens enough to coat the back of a spoon.
Whisk in butter, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken into small cubes or chunks.
Cook all remaining ingredients; add chicken.
Mix a water and flour thickening and add to vegetable and chicken until thickness you like.
Pour into loaf cake pan and top with biscuits.
Bake in 350° oven until biscuits are brown.
Can use canned biscuits, Bisquick mix, etc. for the biscuits.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix together sugar and cream cheese until blended.
Add pumpkin butter, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice.
Blend ingredients together until smooth.
Use for dipping fruit slices.

title: sweet corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, sugar, salt together.
In pan or skillet, melt margarine and let it get hot.
Add corn mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
It is done when it becomes thick.

title: cheesy herbed pork chops
directions: Trim fat from meat.
In a large skillet, cook chops in margarine or butter over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Turn chops and add carrot.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes more or until no pink remains.
Remove chops.

title: twenty-four hour omelet
directions: Butter one side of bread.
Cut bread in about 1 inch cubes.

title: rock cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nanny's pie crust
directions: Whip Spry with water and milk until creamy.
Add flour and salt, a little at a time, until well mixed but doesn't stick to your fingers.
Roll out and place in pie pan.
Flute edges.

title: celia's pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic and cayenne. Spread in pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over the top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, onion and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts and mixture is heated through.
Serve with vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep closed in refrigerator.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In medium saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in three layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, molasses and egg.
Mix in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Cover and refrigerate.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonful into balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar. Place balls, sugar side up, about 3-inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake just until set, 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately move from cookie sheet.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cool and debone chicken.
Mix soups, sour cream and almonds. Melt butter and crumble until butter is taken up.
Top casserole with this and sprinkle with poppy seeds.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
If you double the recipe, leave off 1 can of celery soup.

title: vidalia onion complete casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make alternating layers of onions, potatoes and chicken.
Mix soup and margarine; spread on top. Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted margarine together and press into 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
(A smaller dish can be used.
Cake will be thicker.)
Mix eggs, soft margarine and powdered sugar together and alternate in layers with bananas and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over the top. Refrigerate.

title: garlic gourmet chicken breasts
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
In non-metal container, combine sour cream, lemon juice, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Add chicken to mixture; coat each piece well.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 24 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken from sour cream mixture.
Roll up.
Roll chicken in stuffing, coating evenly.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: blackberry pudding
directions: Cream 1/2 stick butter and sugar.
Add egg, 1 teaspoon of vanilla and dry ingredients, sifted together.
Fold blueberries into flour mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 x 10 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and easy! cookie bars
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted and pour over corn flakes and stir.
Put in pan; let cool and cut.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook carrots for 10 minutes in water, drain and set aside.
Melt butter in large, deep frying pan.
Add onion, celery and basil.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper and flour.
Continue to saute for a few minutes.
Blend in chicken broth.
Turn up heat and cook until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Add chicken, carrots and parsley.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Top with parsley.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: cold tomato soup(gazpacho)
directions: Place all ingredients into a bowl of a food processor.
Blend until no large pieces remain.
Adjust seasonings according to taste by adding more salt and vinegar (if desired).
Chill overnight.
If desired, add garnish of finely chopped green pepper, tomatoes, cucumber and hard-boiled egg.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Roll into balls.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or microwave 5 minutes on High.
Makes about 120.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside. Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat; add eggs and beat again. Add flour alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix well until blended.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and mix well.
Spoon half of batter into lightly greased 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Sprinkle half of cinnamon mixture.
Pour remaining batter.
Sprinkle rest of cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hamburger bean dip
directions: Fry the loose hamburger until thoroughly cooked.
Drain off the excess liquids.
Add seasoning to taste.
Add the taco seasoning mix and directed amount of water.
Simmer as directed. Place mixture into a glass baking dish.
Cover completely with refried beans.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until the beans are hot and the cheese is melted.
Serve hot with corn chips to dip.
(Doritos style chips are recommended.)

title: robbie's cookie bar
directions: Thoroughly combine graham cracker crumbs, flour and baking soda; set aside.
Combine melted margarine and brown sugar; stir in eggs, water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven 16 to 18 minutes or lightly brown.
Remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips over warm surface.
Let stand until chips soften. Spread evenly, let cool completely.
Cut in bars.

title: scones
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in all the butter to get a coarse meal consistency.
Combine buttermilk and currants; add this to the flour mixture.
Turn out on floured board and pat until it holds together, handling as little as possible.
Divide into 6 pieces.
Shape into circles and cut each circle into either 4 to 6 wedges.
Put an egg in a cup and beat it around with a brush until scrambled.
Brush this mixture on top of the scones. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 24 to 36.
Serve with lemon curd, fresh blueberries and whipped cream.

title: applesauce drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; stir in egg.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture, alternating with applesauce. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls; flatten with fork.
Bake at 350°for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add zucchini, nuts, pineapple and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: russian julienne
directions: Cut chicken into strips approximately 2x3-inch. Grease the pan with oil. Layer the pan with chicken first, then rings of onion. Add a layer of sliced mushrooms; topping with a layer of thinly sliced potatoes. Spoon on mayo, spread to cover entire potato layer

title: spice cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cupcake tins with paper baking cups.
Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and milk.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed of mixer.
Scrape bowl and beaters.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into cups, filling each 1/2 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Dust with powdered sugar or frost with favorite frosting.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together in big container.
Store with lid.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix eggs, flour, cottage cheese and cheese.
Pour over vegetables in cake pan; stir together.
Cut up butter over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: molded seafood salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on cold water in saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt, lemon juice and Tabasco.
Cool.
Gradually stir in mayonnaise until blended.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Turn into 3 cup mold or 6 individual molds.
Cover with foil and chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens.
It is easier to unmold if molds are sprayed with Pam before filling.
Serves 6.

title: marzetti redmon style
directions: Saute pepper
and
onion.
Add	ground	beef and brown. Add tomato soup
and
water.
Place
in a 2 quart baking dish. Mix with noodles
and grated cheese, saving a little cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool and slice.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Cook onion in drippings until golden.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Stir bacon and potatoes into mixture and heat through; coat potato slices.
Serve with brats.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: old fashioned corn pudding
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add eggs, corn, butter and salt.
Mix well.
Turn into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place baking dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours or until custard is set.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Melt margarine and add soy sauce.
Put potatoes in nonstick baking sheet.
Pour margarine over potatoes.
Sprinkle with seasoning and bake until crisp, about 1 hour, at 350°.
Calories, 113; sodium, 388 mg.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple chunks with juice in casserole dish. Mix flour, sugar and cheese. Spread over pineapple. Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over mixture.

title: mom's filled cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Add teaspoon of filling, then dab of dough.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Mash with butter, then add other ingredients.
May be put in baking dish to store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: rancho beans
directions: Stir and brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour in 3-quart casserole and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: jello chiffon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: banana bread
directions: *If banana skins are not black, peel and smash yellow bananas and leave on counter at room temperature for 1 - 2 hours.
Set bananas aside.
They will be added in at the end of recipe. Mix together vanilla, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
In a separate bowl combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Spread on buns.
Place open-faced buns on cookie sheet and cover with foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen sandwiches.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Brown ground beef with potatoes and bread crumbs.
Pour corn on top of meat mixture.
Add tomatoes over corn.
Slice onions and place on top of tomatoes.
Cover and simmer until heated through. (May also be fixed without the potatoes.)

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt together and beat oleo and chocolate. Beat all ingredients together in greased pie plate. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: classic family meat loaf(microwave)
directions: In bowl mix thoroughly the 1/2 cup soup, beef, crumbs, onion, 3 teaspoons Worcestershire, egg and pepper.
Microwave in a 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish.

title: peanut butter mini chip loaves
directions: *Or substitute soured fresh milk.
To sour milk, place 1 1/2 tablespoons lemon juice plus enough milk to equal 1 1/2 cups in 2-cup measure.
Stir; let stand 5 minutes before using.

title: party chicken
directions: Clean the chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and a little garlic. Blend other ingredients (not cashews).
Pour over chicken after you have baked the chicken at 400° for 35 minutes. After pouring sauce over chicken, bake another 20 minutes, covered with foil. Garnish with cashews.
Serve with hot rice, green salad with oranges, rolls, champagne and dessert.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown and drain meats.
Cook onion and pepper until tender. Stir in tomato juice, pizza sauce and spice mix.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Set oven at 425°.
Prepare crust; press into 9 x 13-inch pan going halfway up sides of pan.
Cover with 1/2 the meat sauce, then 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat again.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Combine yogurt and Cool whip in a bowl; mix.
Pour into pie crust and freeze 1 hour.
Top with desired fruit.
Serves 8. Makes a cool dessert for summer.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and apples; mix.
Now, add eggs, oil and vanilla; mix.
Pour into a greased and floured pan (11 x 14-inch sheet) and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. May be baked in a smaller pan for a more cake-like texture.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon together.
Cream in butter.
Mix well and add pumpkin.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add salt, pepper, drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes. Add milk and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon in mounds over casserole.
Sprinkle potatoes with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon wellington
directions: Make mushroom onion filling:
Melt butter in a skillet and saute onion until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms and cook, stirring, until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove to bowl to chill.
Filling may be refrigerated up to 2 days or may be frozen.

title: congealed salad
directions: Put milk in refrigerator until it is cold.
Bring pineapple to a boil, cook for 4 minutes.
Then add dry jello.
Cook 3 additional minutes.
Set this mixture aside and let it cool.
Whip the milk with a mixer.
Then add it to the pineapple-jello mixture.
Add cottage cheese and blend well by hand.
Place in refrigerator and let it congeal.

title: fast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water for 5 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar and oil.
Pour in yeast water.
Stir like biscuits.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness and cut with large biscuit cutter.
Fold one edge over a pat of margarine.
Place on greased sheet.
Let set for 1 hour to rise.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Dust fish with flour first, then dip in batter and deep fry.

title: stuffed pecans
directions: Take two pecan	halves	and spread cream cheese between the two.
Put
the
two
halves together to form a "sandwich". Makes 30 appetizers.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Take meat tenderizer mallet and pound lightly the top thick end of the breast on both sides.
Dip breasts in eggs, then dredge in bread crumbs.
In a medium skillet fry breasts in olive oil until golden brown.
Pour 1/4 of spaghetti sauce into glass baking dish.
Place still warm breasts into baking dish.
Cover with remainder of spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted and slightly brown (approximately 20 minutes).

title: raisin wine pie
directions: Rinse raisins, add water, boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in wine; blend sugar and flour, stir and boil for 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in lemon rind, juice and coloring.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Cover with top crust. Flute edges, prick surface with fork.
To glaze, brush egg white over surface.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: In a bowl, combine cornstarch, orange peel, orange juice and mustard.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a wide frying pan over medium heat.
Stir in onion and carrots, then add water.
Cover pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until carrots are tender-crisp (10 to 12 minutes).
Stir cornstarch mixture.
Pour into pan and cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: fettucine
directions: Cook noodles.
Strain and set aside.
Melt butter and add noodles.
Add sour cream and stir a minute over low heat.
Add cream and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add cheese, sprinkling of nutmeg and 1 tablespoon chives.
Continue stirring until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle remaining chives on top before serving.
Serves 4.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: bologna gravy
directions: Chop bologna into small pieces.
Fry bologna in oil till brown.
Turn heat down to medium, and add salt, pepper to taste. Add 3 to 4 tbsp. sifted flour and stir till flour browns slightly. Add milk to desired thickness.
To make sausage gravy, use 12 oz. or 1 lb. sausage, crumble, fry.
Drain and add flour and milk, simmer.

title: quick linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Keep warm.
Meanwhile in medium skillet, heat oil and saute garlic for 3 minutes or until golden. Stir in flour until smooth.
Add clams with juice and parsley to taste.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until sauce is thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
To serve, pour clam sauce over pasta.
Toss to combine.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices and place on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Press slices together to line cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool and remove from foil

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water; drain pineapple.
Save juice.
Mix cranberry sauce and pineapple juice in Jell-O.
Chill until set.
Beat the cream cheese and pineapple.
Spread on top of Jell-O.
Top with nuts.

title: broiled peanut butter frosting
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Beat in milk, then nuts.
Spread over warm cake.
Place frosted cake under broiler, about 4-inches from heat source.
Broil only a few seconds, until topping starts to bubble.
Watch very carefully!! Cool at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: jack-pot casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cook noodles separately.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to water.
Drain.
Mix together meat mixture, noodles, corn and Worcestershire sauce.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon or orange cake
directions: Beat egg whites separately from yellows.
Beat egg yellows, sugar and oil together, then add salt, vanilla, then flour, grated lemon or orange rind and egg whites (beaten very stiff).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake in mold pan.
Use your favorite white icing.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Arrange artichokes in center of baking dish (8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch).
Then arrange mushrooms around the artichokes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs, olives, garlic salt, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper over top and drizzle oil over the top of the whole mixture.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Last 5 minutes of baking, remove the foil so that top can brown.
If you use frozen artichokes, you cook them first according to the directions on the package.

title: candied carrots
directions: Boil carrots until done; drain.
Mix orange juice, honey and brown sugar; bring to a boil.
Slowly add cornstarch and stir until thick.
Pour sauce over carrots.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, celery and onion in smallest amount of water as possible until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries and oranges.
Chop apples and crushed pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Cool.
Add to the fruit mixture.
Refrigerate to allow to thicken.

title: granny martin's mock strawberry preserves
directions: Mash figs. Add sugar and cook 5 minutes after starts to boil. Add Jell-O and cook 2 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Add pasta and Parmesan and mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally. Add broccoli, pepperoni and Mozzarella and toss.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown flour in oil until medium brown.
Add onions, pepper, green onions and garlic to the flour.
Let fry until onions are transparent.
Add tomato sauce.
Rinse can with water and add to mixture.
