Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Lea and Perrins and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer for 20 minutes more.

title: carolyn's party mix
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; stir in Crisco until well blended.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 250° to 275° for about 1 1/2 hour.
Check periodically.
Stir often.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In a medium bowl, blend cream cheese, salad dressing and sugar. Fold in the whipped topping; set aside. In a large mixing bowl, combine pineapple, nuts and cranberry sauce. Gently combine with cream cheese mixture. Spread in a 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Cover and freeze. Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired. Serves 24.

title: talerina
directions: Saute onions and peppers in bacon grease if available. Add the meat, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until brown. Add tomato paste, sauce, tomatoes and chili powder. Cook about 30 minutes. Boil egg noodles and drain.
Mix together the meat mixture, noodles, corn and black olives.
Pour into casserole dish. Grate the cheese over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: moss inn squash au gratin
directions: Boil or steam zucchini in small amount of salted water. Remove from heat and stir with wooden spoon to break into medium pieces.
Pour zucchini in a shallow casserole dish, top with a layer of grated cheese, sprinkle a layer of bread crumbs over the cheese and dot with butter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. This may be made the day or morning before serving and baked at the last minute.

title: james' pancakes
directions: Dissolve soda in milk.
Add to crumbs.
Add egg and beat well. Stir in baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add flour to desired consistency.

title: golden puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add oil, milk and egg.
Beat with a fork until well mixed.
Drop teaspoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown (about 3 minutes).
Drain, then roll in cinnamon sugar or dip in Chocolate Glaze.

title: delicious beef
directions: Stuff with whole garlic and cover with soy sauce.
Cook in crock-pot on high until done.
This is easy, tender, juicy and delicious.

title: chinese salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, green onions, olives, soy sauce, cilantro and hot pepper sauce in medium size bowl.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease with margarine a 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place nuts on bottom.
Partially thaw in refrigerator for several hours the bread dough; slice and place over nuts.
Make slices about 1-inch thick. Mix dry pudding mix, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over dough.
Place 6 tablespoons margarine randomly on top in chucks. Cover with dish towel and let stand overnight on counter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on tray and serve.

title: chocolate nut tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix brownie mix according to package directions; set aside.
Chop nuts finely.
Combine with butter and syrup.
Generously spray mini muffin pan with vegetable oil spray. Spoon nuts into pan and press to form shallow crust.
Nuts will not go up sides of pan, only on bottom.
Place brownie mix on top of nuts.
Bake 13 to 16 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes or until tarts can be easily removed.
Can substitute 9-inch spring-form pan to make one large tart.
Pat nuts in pan bottom and 1/2-inch up side. Cover with brownie mix.
Bake 55 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the sugar, cream cheese and vanilla and spread on crumbs.
Spread pineapple over mixture.
Layer bananas over pineapple.
Top with large container of Cool Whip. Garnish with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: easy chocolate chip cake(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix and milk together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with chocolate chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: quick chicken pasta
directions: Combine ingredients (except spaghetti and sauce) and brown in butter until onion is tender and chicken is not pink.
Add sauce. Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over spaghetti.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in sugar and let cool. Add cold water, concentrate and juice.
Add crushed ice and ginger ale.
Then add sherbet.

title: strawberry pecan salad
directions: Heat pineapple over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O and cool.
Add pecans, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: grape animal chewies
directions: Thaw grape juice. Soften gelatin in the grape juice.

Boil water. Add gelatin mixture and stir until gelatin is dissolved. Remove from heat and pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and chill. When firm, cut into animal shapes with cookie cutters. Wrap individual "animals" in plastic wrap. Serves 8.

title: crustworthy meat loaf
directions: On floured surface, let dough stand, covered, at room temperature 1 hour.
Reserve 1 tablespoon eggs for glaze.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Shape into 9 x 4-inch loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; drain.
Roll dough to 10 x 7-inch rectangle.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Press onto bottom of greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Place meat loaf in center of dough; fold dough ends over loaf.
Cut 6 strips of dough on each side of loaf; cross over top.
Press and seal with water. Brush with reserved egg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with additional heated cheese spread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: canned peppers
directions: Place peppers in a pan of water; cut off stems and cut out seeds.
Place peppers in boiling water; let stand for 30 minutes. Remove peppers.
Place in ice water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef (raw) and eggs (raw).
Add crackers, onion, ketchup, A. 1. sauce and seasonings.
Place in baking dish and bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: sandy's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed, mixing 3 ounces of coconut with the mix. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Immediately after baking, poke holes in cake with a fork and pour can of creme de coconut over cake.
When cake is cool, mix remaining coconut with Cool Whip, icing cake. Then garnish with coconut.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Heat slowly and stir often.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together sugars and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in pecans.
Pour in pastry lined pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 8 or 9-inch pan.

title: dressing for cabbage
directions: Mix and pour over shredded cabbage.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Drain broccoli well. Mix all ingredients. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown. Serves 12.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread dough evenly on a 15-inch stone. Prebake crust for 10 minutes. Take it out and spread refried beans on bottom, then hamburger, salsa and cheese.
Put back in oven for 10 minutes. Take it out and put chopped onion, tomato, olives and lettuce.
Serve warm.
Sour cream is optional.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a big bowl.
Mix in the flour; let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Roll on floured surface into thin rectangle.
Brush melted butter over dough.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over dough.
Roll up; cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces. Put in greased baking pan.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer tortillas, chicken, sauce and cheese until used and end up with cheese.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
The last 15 minutes, take cover off.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oleo and oats. When cool, add the remaining ingredients. Beat well. Place in long cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or more if needed.

title: onion rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Punch down and let rest.
Roll dough into balls size of walnuts.
Dip in butter, then in onion soup mix. Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes before removing.

title: dinah shore's cheesecake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
In small bowl, mix flour, nuts and brown sugar.
Stir in oleo until well blended. Reserve 1/3 cup and pat remaining crumb mixture evenly into pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet over medium-high heat, saute the onion and garlic in the oil until translucent, about 5 minutes.
While the onion and garlic are sauteing, thoroughly combine the sausage, cheese, bread crumbs, sage, oregano, salt and pepper.
When the onion and garlic are done, add them to the mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Set the mushroom caps upside down on a cookie sheet and fill them with mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Check to make sure the stuffing is completely cooked with no pink sausage.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat until smooth the potatoes, sour cream and cream cheese. Add the garlic salt; put in buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter; bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
(Can be frozen and baked at a later date.)

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to stew.
Serve with cooked noodles.

title: aunt sylvia's icing
directions: Stir flour and milk over low heat, constantly stirring until thick.
Let cool completely.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat until granulated sugar is dissolved (with electric mixer).

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry delite
directions: Mix together milk, pineapple, pie filling, Cool Whip and walnuts; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Freeze 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Will keep at least 1 month.
You may cut into squares and after it is frozen, wrap in servings to save room.

title: rocky road s'mores bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined flour and crumbs; mix well.
Press onto bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 16 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine the butter, pancake syrup and ground ginger in saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Add the sliced cooked carrots.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain carrots after cooking.
Mix all other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
In separate pan, cook potatoes covered with water; add peas and carrots (undrained) and browned hamburger.
Thicken with flour and water mixture.

title: sausage potato pizza
directions: In skillet, cook
sausage
until
browned; drain excess fat. Separate crescent dough
into
8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.	Press
over
bottom and up sides to form a crust, seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheese (Cheddar).

title: pecan pie (no crust)
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 or 35 minutes at 325° on top shell in buttered pie plate.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Heat butter, onion, mushrooms, cheese and almonds.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 320° for 40 minutes.

title: egg-chive dip
directions: Finely chop eggs and mix together with other ingredients until well blended.
Add the amount of milk needed for your desired consistency.

title: quick 'n easy pasta dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
In a skillet, heat oil and then saute garlic and pepper until pepper is tender.
Remove from skillet.
Brown beef.
Add pepper and garlic.
Add spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Heat through.
Mix pasta and sauce.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake about 15 minutes or until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the hamburger (or ground chuck). Add the onion and cook until onion is transparent. Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: doesn't fail meringue
directions: Cook cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and water until thick. Set aside to cool.
Beat 3 egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar for each egg white.
Add vanilla to taste.
Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff, then add to cooked mixture.
Spread on pies and brown.

title: microwave venison roast
directions: Cut
pockets
in venison and stuff with a paste made of garlic powder,
cayenne,
black	pepper	and
Worcestershire (amounts according to your taste).
Coat with liquid smoke and sprinkle with
desired seasonings.
Place on a microsafe rack in
a	glass dish.
Cover and cook on High 15 minutes.
Place bacon
on venison
and cook 15 more minutes.	Remove venison; sprinkle with salt and wrap in foil to retain heat.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: In cake pan, mix sugar and flour; set aside.
Mix oil, margarine, water and cocoa in separate bowl.
Pour these ingredients in pan to boil over low heat.
Then after it boils, pour over sugar and flour mixture that has been standing in pan. Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lipton onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bag or bowl add all ingredients.
Shake or stir until evenly coated.
Empty potatoes in shallow baking dish, stirring occasionally until golden brown for 40 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook onion in margarine. Put all ingredients in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smothered salisbury steak
directions: In a large bowl mix ground beef with chopped onion, bell pepper, garlic, parsley flakes, Worcestershire sauce, prepared yellow mustard, egg, salt, pepper and Italian seasoned bread crumbs.
Mix until mixture will hold together.
Form oval shapes. Place shaped steaks into a skillet on medium high heat and brown on all sides.
While steaks are browning, in a separate 2 quart saucepan melt butter and saute onion rings until just beginning to brown.
Set aside.
When steaks are brown, remove to a platter. Pour out 1/2 of the oil, then add flour to remaining oil and stir well.
Continue to stir until flour browns the color of peanut butter.
Add beef stock or water, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Return steaks to skillet and bring to a bubble.
Add onions and butter to skillet, cover and simmer on low for 25 minutes.
Serve.

title: pineapple frosted
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Cool.
Add fruit juices.
Chill.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.
Pour into tall glasses and top with sherbet.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: fresh corn in the husk
directions: Remove any dry outside leaves from corn husks.
Soak corn in cold water for 5 minutes.
Place ears of corn in a dish and cook on High in microwave for 12 minutes.
(For additional ears, allow 3 minutes cooking time on High for each ear of corn.)
Peel husks down from top of ear.
The silk will peel away with the husk.

title: peccinni
directions: Heat oil.
Slice zucchini once lengthwise, then slice crosswise in 1/4-inch slices.
Begin to saute zucchini.
Add pecan pieces and soy sauce.
Cook until softened.
Recipe may be adjusted to your taste.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, cloves and allspice; add to above mixture.
Add the chopped pecans.
Combine and add last the applesauce and baking soda.
Mix thoroughly.
Store, covered, in refrigerator (will keep 2 to 3 weeks).
Fill cupcake cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put onions, onion tops and cheeses through grinder (or cut up fine with a "grater").
Mix well and shape into 3 or 4 balls. Roll in grated walnuts.
Yields 3 to 4 balls.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, bananas, nuts, oil and vanilla.
Stir in cereal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir to break up cereal.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add banana mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix cheeses with Worcestershire sauce and minced onion.
Add chives, then roll in crushed pecans to form a log roll.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Add to pineapple.
Add eggs, water, and vanilla.
Pour into baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle on cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Combine jello and 1 c. boiling water; stirring 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Add 1/2 c. cold water to gelatin.
Chill to the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold yogurt and whipped topping into gelatin.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Place in heavy saucepan with the water and salt.
Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 15 minutes.
In heavy skillet, melt butter.
Stir in flour. Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until sauce is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Fold sauce into potatoes.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and top is slightly browned.

title: hot stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and stem mushrooms.
Place round side down in shallow baking dish.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in the electric skillet.
Brown chicken.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Mix soups and water in the skillet and brown gravy mix.
Add chicken and rice.
Cook at 200° in skillet until rice is done.

title: cucumber boats
directions: Cut cucumbers in half lengthwise; remove seeds, scoop out pulp and chop in bowl.
Cook bacon.
Saute chopped onion in bacon fat. Mix cucumber pulp, chopped mushrooms, beaten egg, salt and pepper. Add bread crumbs to make consistency of mashed potatoes.
Pile mixture back into cucumber shells.
Spread each with 1 tablespoon tomato paste; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oil sugar cookies
directions: Cream both sugars, oil and oleo. Add dry ingredients and eggs; mix well.

Refrigerate or put in freezer a few minutes (this makes dough easier to work with). Roll dough into balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Put a little of batter on bottom of glass so the sugar sticks to the bottom. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: easy ice cream cake
directions: Layer the bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan with 1 1/4 cups of the macaroon crumbs.
Spread the chocolate ice cream evenly over the crumbs.
Sprinkle 4 of the crushed Heath bars over the ice cream.
Dribble with 3 tablespoons of the chocolate syrup and 2 tablespoons of the coffee liqueur.
Cover with the remaining 1 cup macaroons.
Layer the vanilla ice cream over the macaroons. Top with the remaining crushed Heath bar, the 1 tablespoon chocolate syrup and the 1 tablespoon coffee liqueur.
Cover and freeze at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: kathy's famous blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and beat batter until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Spread batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: sesame seed sticks
directions: Cut butter into flour combined with salt and cayenne pepper. Sprinkle ice water over dough and toss with fork until dough holds together as for pastry.
Roll out on floured board to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; sprinkle generously with sesame seed and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Before removing from pan and while still hot, sprinkle with a little salt.
May be frozen.
Yield: about 2 dozen sticks.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Dump all ingredients in bowl and mix well.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and dry okra.
Pack into jars.
Add to each jar 1 teaspoon of dill seed, 1 garlic pod and 1 red pepper.
Bring water, salt and vinegar to a boil.
Pour the water, salt and vinegar over the okra.
Seal and store for 4 weeks.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Combine with fruit in a large bowl and serve chilled.
Serves 4.

title: dave's bachelor jello surprise
directions: Follow the directions on the box of Jell-O carefully and then add the bananas.

title: tangy slaw
directions: Stir up sugar, Miracle Whip and mustard and thin to consistency with milk or cream.
Put on vegetable ingredients and stir.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with Cool Whip, then add other ingredients. Mix well and chill overnight.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix well. Roll into balls the size of a quarter.
May be frozen before baking.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes a bunch.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream all sugars, shortening and pineapple together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop on greased pans by teaspoon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ranch house beans
directions: Saute onion and hamburg and brown.
Then add remaining ingredients and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
(For best flavor, cook in crock-pot on low for 3 to 5 hours.) Mmmmmmmmmmm good!

title: vegetable pork chop saute
directions: Heat skillet.
Add olive oil; brown pork chops on both sides. Add soup, water, wine and Mrs. Dash.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes on low-medium.
Serve with rice and a vegetable or tossed with cooked pasta.
Enjoy!

title: apple cobbler
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix shortening and sugar.
Beat in whole egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately to the creamed mixture.
Beat into a smooth batter.
Mix apples, sugar and nutmeg.
Arrange in bottom of square pan.
(Optional:
Sprinkle with cinnamon.)
Pour batter over the apples; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 30 minute cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda into a large mixing bowl. Heat margarine, water and cocoa to boiling.
Pour into sifted ingredients and mix well.
Beat eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Add to other mixture.
Bake in a sheet pan at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham salad spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: quickie mochi
directions: Bring water and syrup to a boil.
Lower the heat and gradually pour in the mochi flour, stirring constantly.
Mix hard and well. Mixture will harden rapidly.
Form into small patties.
If desired an (sweet bean filling) can be filled into each patty.
To add color, add a few drops of food coloring to the syrup before adding the mochi flour.

title: old fashioned stack cake with dried apples
directions: Wash apples, cover with cold water and let stand overnight. Cook until tender and dry in same water, being careful they don't stick.
Run through sieve; add sugar and spices.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown
meat
with
onion.
Add undrained canned vegetables, then
seasonings and water.
Cook together for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with tortillas.

title: fresh coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cream of coconut with milk.
Add marshmallows.
Cook over low heat in a heavy saucepan until marshmallows melt.
Cool in a bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour or until mixture starts to jell. Beat jelled mixture with electric mixer until frothy.
Carefully, fold in whipped cream.
Blend in 1 cup flaked coconut, by hand. Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over pie and refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: christmas scent
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for as long as you want a good scent.
May be stored in refrigerator and reused.
Do not drink.

title: pickles - from dill to sweet
directions: Drain and slice pickles and pack back into jar.
Bring to a rolling boil the sugar, vinegar and pickling spice.
Pour over pickles in jar.

title: mom's spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in oil; brown meat, then add flour.
Cook and stir until meat is mixed good.
Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese and simmer.
Pour sauce over thin spaghetti. Parmesan cheese is sprinkled on top.

title: hamburger-beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Bake with bacon, top until bacon is done.
Bake at 350°.
Real good.

title: southern tostadas
directions: Drain peas and beans.
In saucepan combine peas, beans, rice, peppers, celery, tomato paste and chili powder.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup cheese. Serve over hot tostadas topped with remaining cheese and toppers.

title: no crust cream cheese cake
directions: Beat all ingredients well except flour.
Blend in flour last of all (very important).
Blend it slowly, 1 tablespoon at a time. Flour and grease a 10-inch pan, then bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fudge bars
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup margarine, brown sugar, vanilla and egg. Combine flour, salt, baking soda and oatmeal.
Add to egg mixture. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup mixture, pressing remaining mixture in bottom of pan.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Saute onions and butter until tender.
Add soup and heat.
Mix with rice and broccoli in a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: custard tarts
directions: Combine flour and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles bread crumbs.
Mix in enough water to form a dough that sticks together.
Shape dough into ball. Cut in half.
Roll out each half on lightly floured surface, until 1/8-inch thick.
Cut 12 circles from each half, using fluted cookie cutter, 3-inches in diameter.
Fit pastry circles into greased muffin cups, pressing sides so they reach rims.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly butter 1 1/2-quart round glass baking dish.
In large bowl, lightly beat eggs with sugar.
Stir in milk, rice, vanilla and lemon peel.
Pour into prepared dish. Place dish in a baking pan (a 9-inch square metal pan will do) on oven shelf; pour boiling water into pan, level to rice pudding mixture in glass dish.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until pudding is creamy thick.
Use any favorite topping such as raspberry sauce or apricot sauce over rice when served.

title: no fuss fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add peanut butter and stir, then add melted butter and flavoring.
Mix well.
Put in a buttered 8 or 9-inch pie dish.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: pink punch
directions: Add water to lemonade to make 8 cups.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix and fill pie shell.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients together until real creamy and velvety looking.
Add the flour and milk slowly and constantly beating consistently.
The more the mixture is mixed, the better. Place in a large tube cake pan (greased well).
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: sunshine dill pickles or sunshine pickles in a jar
directions: Mix salt, alum, vinegar and water together.
Boil and partly cool.
Place one slice of bread in bottom of jar or gallon glass jug.
Fill with dill, carrots, cauliflowerets and pickles, arranging them for color.
Fill jar with brine.
Top with other bread slice.
Put on lid.
Set the jar in the sunshine for 3 days, then refrigerate.
These are ready to eat in 3 days.
Very good!

title: sausage quiche
directions: Put 2 ounces of grated cheese in bottom of unbaked pie shell. Pour in cooked sausage.
Beat eggs and milk with salt and pepper; pour over sausage.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a plastic bag; mix. Place meat in bag and coat well.

title: vegetable fritters
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients into a smooth batter.
Dip bite-size vegetables into batter and drop into hot fat, heated to 370°, until brown.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Trim crusts from bread and place 1/2 in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cream cheese and then remaining bread.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Put a layer of graham crackers and then a layer of pudding mixture.
Repeat.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch two-crust pie. Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix lightly with apples.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: do nothing cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat, mix in pineapple.
Break up 5 slices of bread in casserole.
Pour mixture over bread and mix to coat only.
Bake at 350° oven for 45-60 minutes till golden brown.
(If doubling recipe, a dozen eggs could be used.)

title: salmon patties
directions: Mash up salmon in medium bowl. Add eggs and flour. Mix well. Melt about 3 Tbsp. vegetable shortening in iron skillet. When hot, spoon in rounded tablespoonful of salmon. Fry until golden brown on both sides. Salt to taste. Makes about 12 patties.

title: arroz mexicana
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet; saute rice and meat until rice is golden all over.
Add all vegetables and spices; stir and saute about 5 minutes.
Add tomato and broth plus salt.
Stir; let simmer, covered, about 10 minutes.
Remove cover, stir and cook another 5 or 10 minutes until water is absorbed and rice is soft and fluffy.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream margarine and add sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add potatoes. Sift together flour, salt and cinnamon. Add this to creamed mixture. You may add 1 cup chopped pecans. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans 45 minutes.

title: tomato snacks
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and scoop out middle.
Fill with cottage cheese or guacamole.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan.
Cream together butter and sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
Gently fold in mashed bananas until well mixed, then very gradually stir in mixed dry ingredients.
Move quickly but add just a little at a time.
Fold in nuts.
Spread batter in loaf pan and bake for about 1 hour. Center will spring back to touch.
Toothpick test will be clean and the bread will be pulled away from the sides of the pan.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: easy drop biscuits
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine yogurt, egg substitute and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until golden.
Makes 1 dozen biscuits.

title: dodge's meat balls
directions: Mix together the first 6 items.
Form into balls (approximately 48). Brown meat balls in a large skillet.
Drain grease.
Stir together soup and water.
Pour over meat balls. Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: scotch treats
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter over low heat, stirring constantly, until blended.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until coated.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and press in.

title: kidney stew
directions: Skin and slice kidneys fine; soak in salted water (2 tablespoons) for 1/2 hour.
Drain; soak 5 minutes in fresh water. Drain.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Heat chili and tomato sauce together. Take tortilla and spoon meat in tortilla.
Take chili sauce and spoon over meat.
Put cheese on top and sprinkle with onions if desired.
Roll up and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (that has small amount of sauce on bottom).
Place toothpick in tortillas. Take leftover sauce and pour over enchiladas.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: ridge fields salad dressing
directions: Must be made in blender. In blender put salt, vinegar, onion, sugar and mustard; using low speed to mix, add Wesson oil very slowly. After thoroughly blended; stir in celery seed.

title: johnnie bozzetti casserole
directions: Saute garlic, onion and celery.
Brown meat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, corn and olives.
Boil noodles according to directions; drain.
Combine all ingredients, reserving half the cheese for top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well.

title: company taters
directions: Boil potatoes in skin until done; cool and peel.
Grate potatoes in a large bowl.
Take the remaining ingredients and put them in a medium saucepan over low heat.
When mixture is hot and margarine is melted, pour over potatoes.
Stir until blended. Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done (uncovered).

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare jello and let set until firm.
With an electric mixer, whip in topping and cream cheese; soften cheese first and cut into pieces.
Fold in nuts and let set until firm.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and minced garlic and drain.
Stir tomato juice, tomato paste, sugar, oregano, salt and basil in with hamburger.
Slow boil for 20 to 25 minutes.
Layer with spaghetti like lasagne; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup and juice from beans with 2/3 of onion rings.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes, or until bubbly around edges.
Remove from oven and place other onion rings on top; brown 2 to 3 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Beat graham crackers in mixer until a little more coarse than cornmeal.
Add powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix.
Add oil as needed to hold mixture together.
Pat out in pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut in squares.

title: apricot sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Arrange potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, orange peel, salt and cinnamon in 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in apricot nectar and 1/3 cup water.
Cook and stir on medium-high until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and apricots.
Pour evenly over potatoes.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 25 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 350° on well greased cookie sheet.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Put cranberries and oranges through food grinder.
Add sugar and nuts.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator several hours or days before serving.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands. Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350 until firm and done.

title: spinach salad with prosciutto dressing
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add Prosciutto and garlic; saute 3 minutes.
Add wine, lemon juice and sugar; simmer for 5 minutes.
Transfer to bowl and cool completely. Season with salt and pepper.
Combine spinach, mushrooms, walnuts and cheese in large bowl.
Toss with enough dressing to season. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: perfect lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna noodles as per package directions.
Keep al-dente, meaning fully cooked, but not overly soft.
Keep noodles in cold water until ready to use.
Remove stems from spinach and dry spinach leaves. (Spinach is optional.)
Spread 1/4 cup of pasta sauce evenly over bottom of a 13x9x2 baking pan. Set aside

title: killer burgers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make into hamburger patties.
Grill to your taste.
Melt Monterey Jack cheese on top of burgers (optional).
